xt] Make the test fit the screen\n\n--\n[css-text] Use web-fonts rather than rely on local install\n\n--\n[css-text] Fix test bugs that prevented the ref from matching\n\n--\n[css-text] Fix incorrect unicode codepoint\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 9a7371498674f44d21b42c39b5176333304d544d, ccc9be7f001b032d7b263c2d968d36cb38e72db6, f1d52e3fdbaba266f4a2aaa85d366a736cb5c240, 966e1f37f9493b9f5b740549808478d5e36f4ec8, 08b54593024b0e329fdcad22d6423da0a52101d1, 254f8bea20e034325b5910a9dd76801eb58c1a10\nwpt-pr: 19443\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/hyphens/reference/hyphens-span-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/i18n/css3-text-line-break-baspglwj-083.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/line-break/line-break-anywhere-002.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/overflow-wrap/overflow-wrap-cluster-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/overflow-wrap/overflow-wrap-cluster-002.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/overflow-wrap/reference/overflow-wrap-cluster-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/parsing/letter-spacing-computed.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/shaping/reference/shaping-024-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/shaping/reference/shaping-025-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/text-indent/text-indent-percentage-004.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/text-transform/reference/text-transform-fullwidth-001-ref.xht", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/text-transform/text-transform-fullwidth-001.xht", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/white-space/break-spaces-tab-004.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/white-space/reference/white-space-intrinsic-size-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/white-space/reference/white-space-intrinsic-size-003-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/word-break/word-break-keep-all-005.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/word-break/word-break-keep-all-006.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/word-break/word-break-keep-all-007.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/word-break/word-break-keep-all-008.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a31719fa6b044f4a891c3d0ce058c12b48931a8c", "parents": ["24e89116f6d92c12afa8992bf0ab6cb6244029b3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Rivoal \u003cgit@florian.rivoal.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585325 [wpt PR 19444] - [css-text] remove test for miscategorized character, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[css-text] remove test for miscategorized character\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 5f53a74d4f506229cd9a33b6b927b8ba0cad9645\nwpt-pr: 19444\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/i18n/css3-text-line-break-baspglwj-094.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a30ccf809fef477ccceea94eb93faec5cc5048fc", "parents": ["a31719fa6b044f4a891c3d0ce058c12b48931a8c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xiaocheng Hu \u003cxiaochengh@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585126 [wpt PR 19411] - Support clamp() in CSSNumericValue.parse(), a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nSupport clamp() in CSSNumericValue.parse()\n\nThis patch supports parsing 'clamp(MIN, VAL, MAX)' into a\nCSSNumericValue via the parse() method.\n\nThis was missed in the previous implementation of clamp(), and should be\nthe last missing piece of the implementation.\n\nBug: 825895\nChange-Id: I6da8113d62b1416dc6d3521b58134932b257ca62\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1832147\nCommit-Queue: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Rune Lillesveen \u003cfuthark@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701536}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 3fd2715039595e34fe87f919683ddad32ff88e71\nwpt-pr: 19411\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-typed-om/stylevalue-subclasses/numeric-objects/parse.tentative.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c0457cec2a17d17dd54ab195695a5a134b2db885", "parents": ["a30ccf809fef477ccceea94eb93faec5cc5048fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585126 [wpt PR 19411] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19411\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-typed-om/stylevalue-subclasses/numeric-objects/parse.tentative.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d8b6a89da1d787c36302bcfb70289b178252a201", "parents": ["c0457cec2a17d17dd54ab195695a5a134b2db885"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Joonghun Park \u003cpjh0718@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575720 [wpt PR 18604] - Make table's clientWidth/Height include its border sizes., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nMake table's clientWidth/Height include its border sizes.\n\nBlink doesn't have table wrapper box currently\nwhile Gecko has it,\nso this CL tries to mimic the behavior that\nclientWidth/Height refers to table wrapper box\nwhich doesn't have borders applied to itself\nand table grid box has the borders.\n\nThis CL adds table's border sizes\nto clientWidth/Height\nat |LayoutBox::PixelSnappedClientWidth/Height|.\n\nAs a result of this CL, table's clientWidth/Height\nand offsetWidth/Height are equal now, respectively.\n\nThe corresponding csswg discussion is\nhttps://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/4245.\n\nBug: 560528, 978019\nChange-Id: I2693eaf38b882fe4a41f931ec1312ecf53352f27\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1763510\nCommit-Queue: Joonghun Park \u003cpjh0718@gmail.com\u003e\nReviewed-by: Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: David Grogan \u003cdgrogan@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Mason Freed \u003cmasonfreed@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701557}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 7bc2d379af8ead0a92387253540a6ee2915783a8\nwpt-pr: 18604\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/cssom-view/table-border-collapse-client-width-height.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/cssom-view/table-border-separate-client-width-height.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/cssom-view/table-with-border-client-width-height.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "25fa8a9e18c8cbd88f88a6546a93991e358992db", "parents": ["d8b6a89da1d787c36302bcfb70289b178252a201"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Anne van Kesteren \u003cannevk@annevk.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585304 [wpt PR 19441] - Mark JSON module tests as tentative, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nMark JSON module tests as tentative\n\nSee https://github.com/whatwg/html/pull/4943 for context.\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: bec7ffa28cc69fe8d8fb343fd9184d30ecce3070\nwpt-pr: 19441\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/README.md", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/invalid-content-type.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/invalid-content-type.tentative.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/module.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/module.tentative.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/non-object.any.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/non-object.tentative.any.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/parse-error.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/parse-error.tentative.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/utf8.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/utf8.tentative.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/valid-content-type.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/valid-content-type.tentative.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c1fd5ec1e57a33ef9e732ee1a87420825bfcb0a", "parents": ["25fa8a9e18c8cbd88f88a6546a93991e358992db"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585304 [wpt PR 19441] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19441\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/module.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/module.tentative.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/non-object.any.js.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/non-object.tentative.any.js.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/parse-error.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/parse-error.tentative.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/utf8.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/utf8.tentative.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/valid-content-type.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/scripting-1/the-script-element/json-module/valid-content-type.tentative.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4957831e0f42675e5d19fd43469f7ca3654b4c1", "parents": ["4c1fd5ec1e57a33ef9e732ee1a87420825bfcb0a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xiaocheng Hu \u003cxiaochengh@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585178 [wpt PR 19424] - Add/Revise WPT to reflect resolution of calc() in table layout, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nAdd/Revise WPT to reflect resolution of calc() in table layout\n\nhttps://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/94 made a resolution that\n\n\"Any math expression of a complex type is treated as auto. Simple typed\nthings continue to work as today.\"\n\nThis patch adds new tests and revises existing tests to reflect the\nresolution.\n\nBug: 382725\nChange-Id: I522799b51fdd4a7cfa66e137ae31c68aaf2dea73\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1832619\nCommit-Queue: Xiaocheng Hu \u003cxiaochengh@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701597}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: cda40b6ff20c841a6195e95387d09072db8fd6e3\nwpt-pr: 19424\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-tables/auto-layout-calc-width-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-tables/calc-percent-plus-0px-auto.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-tables/calc-percent-plus-0px-fixed-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-tables/calc-percent-plus-0px-fixed.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-tables/calc-percent-plus-0px.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-tables/fixed-layout-calc-width-001.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ffa86f64139eb8d73dbbe409e9bdc3846a0951c6", "parents": ["f4957831e0f42675e5d19fd43469f7ca3654b4c1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yi Gu \u003cyigu@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584430 [wpt PR 19353] - [ScrollTimeline] Remove CompositingReason::kScrollTimelineTarget, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[ScrollTimeline] Remove CompositingReason::kScrollTimelineTarget\n\nSince we have supported main-thread AnimationWorklet, there is no need\nto promote the scroll-source automatically for ScrollTimeline.\n\nChanges to make:\n  1. Attaching / detaching animation to ScrollTimeline no longer need to\n  trigger compositing update nor paint property update.\n  2. Animations with scroll timeline should fall back to main thread\n  when the scroll source is not composited.\n  3. Now that the scroller is not composited due to ScrollTimeline, it\n  needs be composited by other means to have the fast path tested.\n\nBug: 1008720\nChange-Id: I07dbefeb4e16e8be832b354f0a68bfd7cd0f6ee6\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1825720\nReviewed-by: Xianzhu Wang \u003cwangxianzhu@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Stephen McGruer \u003csmcgruer@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Majid Valipour \u003cmajidvp@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Yi Gu \u003cyigu@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701595}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: db4e38642a419ad31f5999627f1d63d183b01833\nwpt-pr: 19353\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/animation-worklet/worklet-animation-with-scroll-timeline-and-display-none.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/animation-worklet/worklet-animation-with-scroll-timeline.https.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bb30c80321baabe146cacd464b4af94787f3b1e5", "parents": ["ffa86f64139eb8d73dbbe409e9bdc3846a0951c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585391 [wpt PR 19447] - [LayoutNG] Include empty/space-only trailing spans, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Include empty/space-only trailing spans\n\nThis patch changes |NGLineBreaker| to include empty or space-\nonly trailing spans into the line.\n\nSuch spans were thought not observable, but it turned out\nthat they are in a few cases; e.g.,:\na. The space is wrapped in an inline box with borders; e.g.,\n      text\u003cspan style=\"border: 1px solid\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003etext\nb. When it is not collapsed (e.g., `pre-wrap`) and is in an\n   inline box with background.\n\nOpen tags are in most cases not-trailable but sometimes they\nare. Before this change, |NGLineBreaker| assumed open tags\nare not-trailable, and handles exceptional cases separately.\nThis patch changes open tags to be trailable. Then non-\ntrailable open tags were removed after the line breaking was\ndetermined. With this chagne, the rare logic runs only once\nfor each wrapped line.\n\nThis patch:\n1. Split over-loaded `kTrailing` state to `kOverflow` and\n   `kTrailing`. This simplifies the conditions when each\n   state can transit to other states.\n2. Re-implemented negative margins[r674177]. The logic became\n   simpler because open tags are now trailable by default.\n3. Re-implemented hanging trailing space fix[r674430]. In\n   addition to the fix, this patch handles trailing spaces in\n   a span. We do not handle multiple space nodes yet as in\n   TODO(crbug.com/1009936) comment, but this change moves one\n   step closer to support it.\n\n[r674177]: https://crrev.com/c/1684243\n[r674430]: https://crrev.com/c/1662451\n\nBug: 1001241, 1003184\nChange-Id: Ife2f8470a510f6e006da9d2397df5c5153e3abd1\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1826063\nCommit-Queue: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701601}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 1239af63c689316e7485d02b4377dcb78ff71a83\nwpt-pr: 19447\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/white-space/trailing-space-position-001.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b0aea144d2c18bc2f4bb977374cf9ceebb05ca80", "parents": ["bb30c80321baabe146cacd464b4af94787f3b1e5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585391 [wpt PR 19447] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19447\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-text/white-space/trailing-space-position-001.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d030970f67ff956164253bb28943465b1af716ca", "parents": ["b0aea144d2c18bc2f4bb977374cf9ceebb05ca80"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585318 [wpt PR 19442] - Set up inline continuations correctly when not inserting a new child., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nSet up inline continuations correctly when not inserting a new child.\n\nLayoutInline::ChildBecameNonInline() is called when a child of an inline\nbecomes in-flow block-level (e.g. when its position changes from\nabsolute to static) and we need to set up a continuation chain because\nof this. Part of this operation is to wrap the in-flow block-level child\ninside a new anonymous containing block.\n\nAddChildIgnoringContinuation(), which is what we call when inserting new\nchildren, did a few nice things to such anonymous containing blocks,\nwhich ChildBecameNonInline() didn't do, most crucially, setting the\nposition of the anonymous containing block to relative if the inline is\nrelatively positioned (to contain absolutely positioned descendants). So\nif the continuation was set up as a reaction to something becoming\nblock-level, rather than being set up as part of inserting new children,\nthe anonymous containing block of block-level children of the inline\ndidn't get position:relative, which made any absolutely positioned\nchildren escape its relatively positioned inline parent, and find a\ncontaining block further up (the viewport, in the included testcase).\n\nTo fix this, break out the code that sets up such an anonymous block\ninto a separate method, and have ChildBecameNonInline() call it.\n\nBug: 732397\nChange-Id: I06b120c3173403ba6db3b93019e95a66575ba0e1\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1833581\nReviewed-by: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701646}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 4da059cdc29ce8ca2b717c53ab7f5a68a4cb7583\nwpt-pr: 19442\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/positioning/toogle-abspos-on-relpos-inline-child.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c344117e2fcb6f574077d9354077ec0615ea3e49", "parents": ["d030970f67ff956164253bb28943465b1af716ca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585318 [wpt PR 19442] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19442\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/CSS2/positioning/toogle-abspos-on-relpos-inline-child.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "27faa24d9911991edf0052157409cf740eb6ba32", "parents": ["c344117e2fcb6f574077d9354077ec0615ea3e49"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L. David Baron \u003cdbaron@dbaron.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585423 [wpt PR 19451] - Sync Mozilla CSS tests as of 2019-10-01, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nSync Mozilla CSS tests as of https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/rev/9a4d6aacc48080f019024c02ac7da1fd576b39fe . (#19451)\n\nThis contains changes from:\n* [bug 1384266](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1384266) by @bradwerth, reviewed by @dholbert\n* [bug 1510486](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1510486) by @BorisChiou, reviewed by @hiikezoe\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 86b568c79fdf6b0e28cebd8f0b00088d03f4e8da\nwpt-pr: 19451\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/flexbox/flexbox-align-self-baseline-horiz-008-ref.xhtml", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/flexbox/flexbox-align-self-baseline-horiz-008.xhtml", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/flexbox/reftest.list", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/will-change/reftest.list", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/will-change/will-change-fixpos-cb-translate-1.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/will-change/will-change-stacking-context-translate-1.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4322c3a841db2227506c6a926854df2b4cd990a", "parents": ["27faa24d9911991edf0052157409cf740eb6ba32"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585423 [wpt PR 19451] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19451\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/will-change/will-change-fixpos-cb-translate-1.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/will-change/will-change-stacking-context-translate-1.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3d8f987cf2c1ef157fc90d971a4c0c3e93d6bf56", "parents": ["f4322c3a841db2227506c6a926854df2b4cd990a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Wang \u003cfwang@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585419 [wpt PR 19450] - Add tests for MathML features that we might remove from Core / unship\u2026, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nAdd tests for MathML features that we might remove from Core / unship from browsers (#19450)\n\nhttps://github.com/mathml-refresh/mathml/issues/27\nhttps://github.com/mathml-refresh/mathml/issues/29\nhttps://github.com/mathml-refresh/mathml/issues/2\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: d9e0e15247ca5269b4e2c9060f38416c2068997b\nwpt-pr: 19450\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/mathml/presentation-markup/fractions/frac-legacy-bevelled-attribute.tentative-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/mathml/presentation-markup/fractions/frac-legacy-bevelled-attribute.tentative.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/mathml/presentation-markup/mrow/legacy-mfenced-element-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/mathml/presentation-markup/mrow/legacy-mfenced-element-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/mathml/presentation-markup/scripts/subsup-legacy-scriptshift-attributes-001.tentative-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/mathml/presentation-markup/scripts/subsup-legacy-scriptshift-attributes-001.tentative.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f3f6dad0dad824e643e833dfd3bcc0ebdec1f28e", "parents": ["3d8f987cf2c1ef157fc90d971a4c0c3e93d6bf56"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585419 [wpt PR 19450] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19450\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/mathml/presentation-markup/fractions/frac-legacy-bevelled-attribute.tentative.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/mathml/presentation-markup/mrow/legacy-mfenced-element-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/mathml/presentation-markup/scripts/subsup-legacy-scriptshift-attributes-001.tentative.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dbfe462c730d0b0d2af6a3f7c513dbf34772ac96", "parents": ["f3f6dad0dad824e643e833dfd3bcc0ebdec1f28e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fredrik S\u00f6derquist \u003cfs@opera.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585388 [wpt PR 19446] - Fix SMIL interval restarting, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nFix SMIL interval restarting\n\nWhen an interval restarts we won't necessarily get a new interval, but\njust adjust the current interval (which could then potentially end).\nChange CheckAndUpdateInterval(...) to reflect this, and narrow the\nrestart criteria in UpdateActiveState(...).\nUpdateActiveState(...) was also only checking for\n\"inactive\" -\u003e \"active/frozen\" transitions to 'begin', but we need to\ncheck for transitions from \"frozen\" as well.\nAlso re-order the check for 'end' so that it is before the one 'begin'.\nThis will mean that events should get dispatched like:\n\n  'begin', 'end', 'begin' and 'end'\n\nwhen we encounter a restart (like in the testcase),\nrather than as previously:\n\n  'begin', 'begin', 'end' and 'end'.\n\nBug: 998526\nChange-Id: I56b2391fdcc22f3a22332d6eeb6aa469225497f6\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1821922\nCommit-Queue: Fredrik S\u00f6derquist \u003cfs@opera.com\u003e\nReviewed-by: Stephen Chenney \u003cschenney@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701710}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 0775b1b524062b8023fcc71d5ae475cb87cfbaa6\nwpt-pr: 19446\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/svg/animations/interval-restart-events.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f8374f10070c47dc97310e39eded68326f54c9be", "parents": ["dbfe462c730d0b0d2af6a3f7c513dbf34772ac96"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584655 [wpt PR 19382] - [LayoutNG] Fix inline-block overflow, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Fix inline-block overflow\n\nScrolling overflow for line boxes was being computed\nincorrectly. The block_end padding was being added\nto linebox's scroll overflow. It should have been\nadded to linebox border box instead.\n\nWhile investigating the standards that define\nthis behavior, I noticed that csswg has resolved\nthat both inline_padding and block_padding should\nbe used for overflow.\n\nThe existing code only used inline_padding. This did\nnot cause an error because block_padding was being added\nsomewhere else. I investigated, and it seems that\nblock_padding got added to layout_result.IntrinsicBlockSize(),\nwhich then got passed to box_-\u003eComputeLayoutOverflow()\nI am not sure of why this is being done, and why it works.\nI think that adding LayoutUnder() when we are explicitly\ncomputing overflow is the right thing to do. It'll make\nthis code work when we switch to pure NG overflow\ncomputation.\n\nBug: 1003373\nChange-Id: I39b8399de463e9e9f1a2c4d906362b14f9a783ca\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1829490\nCommit-Queue: Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701722}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 50bd3712c2028e49a83d961a691d0ed1f7c7dbac\nwpt-pr: 19382\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-overflow/overflow-padding.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e111506432fcb8252f5c838887e03514e7aeaa9", "parents": ["f8374f10070c47dc97310e39eded68326f54c9be"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584655 [wpt PR 19382] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19382\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-overflow/overflow-padding.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "80721d621f5b97f7158eefa56043355aaae24626", "parents": ["2e111506432fcb8252f5c838887e03514e7aeaa9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585424 [wpt PR 19452] - [LayoutNG] Fix static position of positioned objects in RTL, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Fix static position of positioned objects in RTL\n\nBlock-level out-of-flow objects are placed at the start edge\nof the next line if preceded by in-flow inline content, or\nof the current line otherwise.\n\nBefore this change, the \"preceded\" was determined by the\nvisual order. This patch fixes this by using the logical\norder.\n\nBug: 1005149, 1005433, 1002479\nChange-Id: I8589d0daa24021a8106d98770e83629ff9f02c57\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1833366\nCommit-Queue: Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Ian Kilpatrick \u003cikilpatrick@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701741}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: bd731e3cdaccb828eeb8deed9970ecee5cbda2d4\nwpt-pr: 19452\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/positioning/abspos-block-level-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/positioning/abspos-block-level-001.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b4e2d2c2d4b3b9314fc74d3f4e7a0860aa1dc24", "parents": ["80721d621f5b97f7158eefa56043355aaae24626"], "tags": []}, {"author": "jugglinmike \u003cmike@mikepennisi.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585083 [wpt PR 19403] - [docs] Use supported syntax highlight name, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[docs] Use supported syntax highlight name (#19403)\n\nA recent addition to the project documentation specifies \"svg\" as the\ndesired syntax for a number of examples [1]. However, the package used\nto provide syntax highlighting (\"pygments\" from Python) does not\nrecognize SVG, so the new examples introduced the following error:\n\n    Warning, treated as error:\n    docs/writing-tests/test-templates.md:55:Pygments lexer name u'svg' is not known\n\nUpdate the examples to instead request generic XML highlighting.\n--\n\nwpt-commits: e33c216e635b4615e4332953fcb758f698ecd510\nwpt-pr: 19403\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/docs/writing-tests/test-templates.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8040231667e41c52d516fd0e8c8aa7c2ac13acc7", "parents": ["9b4e2d2c2d4b3b9314fc74d3f4e7a0860aa1dc24"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Cooper \u003calcooper@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581791 [wpt PR 19119] - Update xr feature policy name and behavior to match spec, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate xr feature policy name and behavior to match spec\n\nAs a result of TPAC there were some spec changes to the xr feature\npolicy (FP). These were made in:\nhttps://github.com/immersive-web/webxr/pull/842\nThe following changes were needed to become spec compliant:\n\n* rename FP from \"xr\" to \"xr-spatial-tracking\"\n* supportsSession always resolves for \"inline\"\n* supportsSession rejects for immersive-vr with a SecurityError if FP\n  not set\n* default features per mode are now required features for that mode\n* requestSession does not unconditionally reject if FP is not set,\n  instead resolving specific features now depends on FP status.\n* While resolving features, if any required features depend on a missing\n  FP, the requestSession call will fail with a \"NotSupportedError\"\n* While resolving features, if any optional features depend on a missing\n  FP, those features will be silently ignored.\n* devicechange events will not fire for documents that do not have\n  FP set.\n\nBug: 1003842\nChange-Id: Ie9ae16b5c1d863b730e556b511c024bae8a4503c\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1808800\nCommit-Queue: Alexander Cooper \u003calcooper@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Brandon Jones \u003cbajones@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Ian Clelland \u003ciclelland@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Jacob DeWitt \u003cjacde@chromium.org\u003e\nAuto-Submit: Alexander Cooper \u003calcooper@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701740}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: dc17f8c8e3372dd30ce98d542874843f87726e8e\nwpt-pr: 19119\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/feature-policy/reporting/xr-report-only.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/feature-policy/reporting/xr-report-only.https.html.headers", "testing/web-platform/tests/feature-policy/reporting/xr-reporting.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/feature-policy/reporting/xr-reporting.https.html.headers", "testing/web-platform/tests/webxr/resources/webxr_util.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/webxr/webxr-supported-by-feature-policy.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webxr/webxr_feature_policy.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webxr/webxr_feature_policy.https.html.headers"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0d34ec0cb3b41dbc57243f1ebc1e77a840bba80e", "parents": ["8040231667e41c52d516fd0e8c8aa7c2ac13acc7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1581791 [wpt PR 19119] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19119\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/webGLCanvasContext_create_xrcompatible.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/webGLCanvasContext_makecompatible_contextlost.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/webxr-supported-by-feature-policy.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/webxr_feature_policy.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_requestSession_immersive_no_gesture.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_requestSession_immersive_unsupported.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_requestSession_no_mode.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_requestSession_non_immersive_no_gesture.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_requestSession_requiredFeatures_unknown.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_supportsSession_immersive.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_supportsSession_immersive_unsupported.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrDevice_supportsSession_non_immersive.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrSession_features_deviceSupport.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrSession_prevent_multiple_exclusive.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrSession_viewer_availability.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrWebGLLayer_constructor.https.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "825d060e34af2a3fd97dc5b7d437c20e078290e9", "parents": ["0d34ec0cb3b41dbc57243f1ebc1e77a840bba80e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jacob DeWitt \u003cjacde@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585432 [wpt PR 19453] - Reland \"Update emulated position on each XRFrame\", a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nReland \"Update emulated position on each XRFrame\"\n\nCL https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1808086,\nwhich conflicted with this one has been reverted, which means this CL\ncan be relanded as-is.\n\nThis is a reland of 8be89ae08126913ff4447927ac5a087b8d6babcf\n\nOriginal change's description:\n\u003e Update emulated position on each XRFrame\n\u003e\n\u003e For both the head poses and input poses, send this value through mojo\n\u003e from the device process to the renderer process on every frame.\n\u003e\n\u003e Bug: 969131\n\u003e Change-Id: Ie895deb75bddb6dd883d09828cfcb30f335d3793\n\u003e Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1825478\n\u003e Auto-Submit: Jacob DeWitt \u003cjacde@chromium.org\u003e\n\u003e Commit-Queue: Will Harris \u003cwfh@chromium.org\u003e\n\u003e Reviewed-by: Will Harris \u003cwfh@chromium.org\u003e\n\u003e Reviewed-by: Klaus Weidner \u003cklausw@chromium.org\u003e\n\u003e Reviewed-by: Alexander Cooper \u003calcooper@chromium.org\u003e\n\u003e Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701389}\n\nBug: 969131\nChange-Id: Ib6ea499fbc081962e5572591258c1247d057279f\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1834202\nReviewed-by: Klaus Weidner \u003cklausw@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Will Harris \u003cwfh@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Jacob DeWitt \u003cjacde@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Jacob DeWitt \u003cjacde@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701782}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 3bbc437f5434aff6864ee7458f8f24d1e503eda7\nwpt-pr: 19453\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/resources/chromium/webxr-test.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/webxr/getViewerPose_emulatedPosition.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webxr/xrInputSource_emulatedPosition.https.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f165d1715a8dd625a17d2e28e0f2693405c7c1f", "parents": ["825d060e34af2a3fd97dc5b7d437c20e078290e9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585432 [wpt PR 19453] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19453\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/getViewerPose_emulatedPosition.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webxr/xrInputSource_emulatedPosition.https.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8416bec7fc1ced3b754ca1ae12f0d3a017a15eea", "parents": ["8f165d1715a8dd625a17d2e28e0f2693405c7c1f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eric Willigers \u003cericwilligers@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585281 [wpt PR 19437] - CSS: Test -webkit-radial-gradient with missing comma before color list, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nCSS: Test -webkit-radial-gradient with missing comma before color list\n\nBlink and Safari tolerate an omitted comma before the color list\nin -webkit-radial-gradient, contrary to compatibility spec.\n\n(Edge 18 and Firefox require the comma.)\n\nhttps://www.w3.org/TR/2011/WD-css3-images-20110217/#radial-gradients\nhttps://compat.spec.whatwg.org/#css-gradients-webkit-radial-gradient\n\nNote this doesn't affect radial-gradient().\n\nBug: 1010278\n\nChange-Id: Ib4f0f5fae70f21b34fa922125271add39ea379c4\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1833197\nCommit-Queue: Eric Willigers \u003cericwilligers@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Rune Lillesveen \u003cfuthark@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701788}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 2c680dfc22c8c0ad0afa4243974f59b2ea4f1dfc\nwpt-pr: 19437\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/compat/webkit-gradient-comma.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/compat/webkit-radial-gradient-radii.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec6af685e02902a3cc649e19d419900f2c497378", "parents": ["8416bec7fc1ced3b754ca1ae12f0d3a017a15eea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585281 [wpt PR 19437] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19437\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/compat/webkit-radial-gradient-radii.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "46b1392b9937d63fa9cd76aafcf65fed89472b5e", "parents": ["ec6af685e02902a3cc649e19d419900f2c497378"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Philip J\u00e4genstedt \u003cphilip@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585475 [wpt PR 19456] - [GitHub Actions] remove the update-pr-preview job, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[GitHub Actions] remove the update-pr-preview job (#19456)\n\nAs discovered in https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/issues/19378,\nthe existing setup isn't compatible with the GitHub Actions read-only tokens\nfor pull requests from forks.\n\nSince the location of the staging deployment isn't very discoverable even\nwhen it does work, disable the job pending a new setup.\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 81b79d799e8f87639725ef965ac16b436b7498bb\nwpt-pr: 19456\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/.github/workflows/pull_request.yml", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/ci/tests/test_update_pr_preview.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/ci/update_pr_preview.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/tox.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c670cc39b282dd3ca862302210f3da89fda10cf", "parents": ["46b1392b9937d63fa9cd76aafcf65fed89472b5e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Rivoal \u003cgit@florian.rivoal.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585518 [wpt PR 19460] - [css-text] Two different-looking tests were sharing a reference, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[css-text] Two different-looking tests were sharing a reference\n\nGet them their own ref each\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: e9ba0321716ad1b3c853f4de4c17da832411412d\nwpt-pr: 19460\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/hyphens/hyphens-out-of-flow-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/hyphens/reference/hyphens-out-of-flow-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-text/hyphens/reference/hyphens-span-001-ref.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "461de363cb3738f4ebc8bde4ff97376c66ea8aae", "parents": ["5c670cc39b282dd3ca862302210f3da89fda10cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585518 [wpt PR 19460] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19460\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-text/hyphens/hyphens-out-of-flow-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-text/hyphens/hyphens-span-001.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0c4e8e8b45cdda699d199d346df1eb7384987006", "parents": ["461de363cb3738f4ebc8bde4ff97376c66ea8aae"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Reilly Grant \u003creillyg@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585506 [wpt PR 19458] - [usb] Allow device-scope control transfers when unconfigured, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[usb] Allow device-scope control transfers when unconfigured\n\nThis change updates Blink to match the WebUSB specification in allowing\ncontrol transfers with the recipient set to 'device' or 'other' when the\ndevice is in an unconfigured state.\n\nMore test cases are added to exercise control transfer parameter\nvalidation.\n\nBug: 1009886\nChange-Id: I423a4307878714e07a62ef66715eb0c5b4f4d08d\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1834649\nReviewed-by: Matt Reynolds \u003cmattreynolds@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Reilly Grant \u003creillyg@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701894}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: e8c6799e1274232e896f58e183529911fcf11e7e\nwpt-pr: 19458\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/resources/chromium/webusb-test.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/webusb/usbDevice.https.any.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aceb2a308aa85d986f93d0cb0186fa0ca1554060", "parents": ["0c4e8e8b45cdda699d199d346df1eb7384987006"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585506 [wpt PR 19458] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19458\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/webusb/usbDevice.https.any.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6489afd225437aa273d4430839565f4c366d9228", "parents": ["aceb2a308aa85d986f93d0cb0186fa0ca1554060"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Philip J\u00e4genstedt \u003cphilip@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584513 [wpt PR 19368] - Add foolip as reviewer for GitHub directory, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nAdd foolip as reviewer for GitHub directory\n--\n\nwpt-commits: b2a553bbb39d11f07b839c333a28b17e8f718ea4\nwpt-pr: 19368\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/.github/META.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "070b611d8df55e8df971bc5a9487ab5084d4ce3b", "parents": ["6489afd225437aa273d4430839565f4c366d9228"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olivier Yiptong \u003coyiptong@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584292 [wpt PR 19330] - [Native File System] Aborting a directory iteration succeeds, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[Native File System] Aborting a directory iteration succeeds\n\nThe return statement of the async iterator was not returning the\nexpected type. This removes the ability to cancel an iteration\nwhich fixes the bug where an error would be thrown otherwise.\n\nA full implementation of directory iteration will re-implement\nthis functionality correctly.\n\nBUG=1007509\n\nChange-Id: I77f3b76b117b7df939e73da826f4fc9b82e9441e\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1826993\nCommit-Queue: Olivier Yiptong \u003coyiptong@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Marijn Kruisselbrink \u003cmek@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701356}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 6c043ae7c1c6edb9c6c329a1c2a559d6da4e45ae\nwpt-pr: 19330\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/native-file-system/native_FileSystemDirectoryHandle-getEntries.tentative.https.manual.window.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/native-file-system/sandboxed_FileSystemDirectoryHandle-getEntries.tentative.https.any.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/native-file-system/script-tests/FileSystemDirectoryHandle-getEntries.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "360a94b12f3bfa2594e84125b6cb4a2715080907", "parents": ["070b611d8df55e8df971bc5a9487ab5084d4ce3b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584292 [wpt PR 19330] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19330\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/native-file-system/native_FileSystemDirectoryHandle-getEntries.tentative.https.manual.window.js.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/native-file-system/sandboxed_FileSystemDirectoryHandle-getEntries.tentative.https.any.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eba0611ad29932045d69580169898e8a4b7fa4f1", "parents": ["360a94b12f3bfa2594e84125b6cb4a2715080907"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585130 [wpt PR 19412] - Port rotate-interpolation.html to wpt, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nPort rotate-interpolation.html to wpt\n\nThere is already a rotate-interpolation.html under wpt/. This CL adds\nmore test cases to it.\n\nBug: 900581\nChange-Id: I4bfc7678d2ec266e243394f4886c0ad7f03497d7\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1832561\nReviewed-by: Yi Gu \u003cyigu@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701546}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 64e0fbcb8fc1322148b712026ed5c4dafb173544\nwpt-pr: 19412\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-transforms/animation/rotate-interpolation.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f445aebc13ed55981bcd2e7a136f41e0513f801", "parents": ["eba0611ad29932045d69580169898e8a4b7fa4f1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585130 [wpt PR 19412] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19412\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transforms/animation/rotate-interpolation.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f30b269b5815731fcd261a342aabbf7684819d5", "parents": ["9f445aebc13ed55981bcd2e7a136f41e0513f801"], "tags": []}, {"author": "autofoolip \u003cauto@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585509 [wpt PR 19459] - Update interfaces/css-typed-om.idl, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate interfaces/css-typed-om.idl (#19459)\n\nSource: https://github.com/tidoust/reffy-reports/blob/075d00f/ed/idl/css-typed-om.idl\nBuild: https://travis-ci.org/tidoust/reffy-reports/builds/592320118\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 06cdd9b89e6a4066c5ef629237bb3b847b1009ed\nwpt-pr: 19459\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/interfaces/css-typed-om.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e6485c7f3e608de024fe82f418b1bef87e64412d", "parents": ["8f30b269b5815731fcd261a342aabbf7684819d5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Adam Rice \u003cricea@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584445 [wpt PR 19357] - Implement abort for WebSocketStream handshake, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nImplement abort for WebSocketStream handshake\n\nThe WebSocketStream explainer describes being able to pass an\nAbortSignal object to the WebSocketStream constructor to abort the\nhandshake. This wasn't implemented yet in Blink. Implement it.\n\nBug: 983030\nChange-Id: I9d96bf145a4978867dd8ae98a13af9ad9cff752c\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1827116\nReviewed-by: Yutaka Hirano \u003cyhirano@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Adam Rice \u003cricea@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701971}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: c0bc582f0f5dd6e42e4231665cf4dea8a8783eae\nwpt-pr: 19357\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/websockets/stream-tentative/abort.any.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "21a76bd16a43e4654ab252fade77e593d65e9710", "parents": ["e6485c7f3e608de024fe82f418b1bef87e64412d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584445 [wpt PR 19357] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19357\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/websockets/stream-tentative/abort.any.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1278f4cbcb6e569880e0ab59e0ddeeb38e841107", "parents": ["21a76bd16a43e4654ab252fade77e593d65e9710"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Carlos Alberto Lopez Perez \u003cclopez@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1575589 [wpt PR 18595] - Add Dockerfile for WebKitGTK testing (based on Debian), a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nAdd Dockerfile for WebKitGTK testing based on Debian (#18595)\n\nThis adds a new Dockerfile that will be used for tests\nwith webkitgtk_minibrowser on taskcluster.\n\nThe image is configured to install the WebKitGTK packages\nfrom a repository at https://webkitgtk.org/debian\nThis repository will provide updated packages of WebKitGTK\nreleases with experimental features enabled.\n(some of this features need to be enabled at build-time,\ntherefore the need for custom builds)\n\nThe image is based on Debian 10 (Buster) instead of Ubuntu,\nbecause the current release bot at build.webkit.org [1]\nruns Debian 10. And having this image match what this bot\nruns, will allow binary compatibility with the built products\nthis bot is producing. The idea is (in a next patch) try\nto download and use those products to run WPT tests with\nthe nightly builds from webkitgtk trunk/ToT.\n\n[1] https://build.webkit.org/builders/GTK%20Linux%2064-bit%20Release%20%28Build%29\n--\n\nwpt-commits: abb820ae83ffb82ccd8380ce61685b51329a7b07\nwpt-pr: 18595\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/docker/Dockerfile.webkitgtk", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/docker/README.md", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/docker/start.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0319a4db07fe470d7603943d22a550f3c0ae1fe6", "parents": ["1278f4cbcb6e569880e0ab59e0ddeeb38e841107"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Harald Alvestrand \u003chta@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585444 [wpt PR 19454] - Fix iceConnectionState test to accept \"completed\" state, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nFix iceConnectionState test to accept \"completed\" state\n\nWhile waiting for \"connected\" state on PC2, PC1 may sometimes have\ntime to transit to \"completed\" state. This CL accepts both event\nsequences.\n\nDue to the bug on not completing, this will only happen in plan B.\nDelete the mac-specific expectations files.\n\nBug: 997201\nChange-Id: I7aab5566c7868990d840bda9afc16516cf147425\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1834225\nCommit-Queue: Harald Alvestrand \u003chta@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Henrik Bostr\u00f6m \u003chbos@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702034}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: a195d5763c5b640c04b00cb0ed895f4b33bbf37a\nwpt-pr: 19454\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/webrtc/RTCPeerConnection-iceConnectionState.https.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "38e1af9ae094964e3b83cd9ad78fe3d8b8398e6a", "parents": ["0319a4db07fe470d7603943d22a550f3c0ae1fe6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Stephen McGruer \u003csmcgruer@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585402 [wpt PR 19448] - Fix interfaces/Document/getAnimations.html test, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nFix interfaces/Document/getAnimations.html test\n\nThis test was assuming that the iframe load event could not fire during\nappendChild, which it does on Chrome. To fix this, setup the promise\nbefore calling appendChild, but only await on it afterwards.\n\nBug: None\nChange-Id: Ie5ebdd7cec0fe0c276621033afaa8e8a5699dad1\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1833902\nReviewed-by: Kevin Ellis \u003ckevers@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Stephen McGruer \u003csmcgruer@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702037}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 4786b7387504f691ead311c58c2da512ced8472d\nwpt-pr: 19448\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/web-animations/interfaces/Document/getAnimations.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "63c731ad93f93c06d2c0443f69e4aa49e79c7ecd", "parents": ["38e1af9ae094964e3b83cd9ad78fe3d8b8398e6a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "autofoolip \u003cauto@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585752 [wpt PR 19474] - Update interfaces/webrtc-stats.idl, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate interfaces/webrtc-stats.idl (#19474)\n\nSource: https://github.com/tidoust/reffy-reports/blob/2ceecfb/ed/idl/webrtc-stats.idl\nBuild: https://travis-ci.org/tidoust/reffy-reports/builds/592710942\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 8c0e66a831a3ef62f5f427dd6656bb8f076cbf42\nwpt-pr: 19474\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/interfaces/webrtc-stats.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "98e754d9fe4b134ef96e99d92247e69c0ee10f93", "parents": ["63c731ad93f93c06d2c0443f69e4aa49e79c7ecd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584870 [wpt PR 19391] - Port box-shadow-interpolation.html to wpt, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nPort box-shadow-interpolation.html to wpt\n\nBug: 900581\nChange-Id: I227b90e5ab5088f76d4b51caa971b7edcc3a8a26\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1830592\nReviewed-by: Stephen McGruer \u003csmcgruer@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702139}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 90acc7f2217913be4abd6ee6bd5bd70e36d32c6a\nwpt-pr: 19391\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-backgrounds/animations/box-shadow-interpolation.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4c0bd2e932f61feb4e4cfe6a927337461ceb0cf", "parents": ["98e754d9fe4b134ef96e99d92247e69c0ee10f93"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584683 [wpt PR 19383] - [LayoutNG] Fix replaced abspos with no intrinsic size, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Fix replaced abspos with no intrinsic size\n\nOne more abspos edge case:\nReplaced element, with no intrinsic size, but with\nintrinsic aspect ratio.\n\nThe example problem here is an SVG with aspect ratio,\nbut no intinsic size. According to the spec, its\ninline size should fill container, and block size\nshould be derived from inline size and aspect ratio.\n\nExisting code did not handle this case. If element\nhad no size, its size would be computed and get clamped\nby minmax.\n\nA replaced element with no size gets a default minmax of\n300x150, so elements would effectively get clamped to minmax.\n\nMy fix is a bit of a hack. It uses absence of minmax as a signal\nthat size should not be clamped.\n\nThe intrinsic size handling is surprisingly complex for replaced\nelements. I wonder if there  are any other parts of NG that\nneed a close look in how replaced with aspect ratio/no size\nare handled.\n\nFF handles this correctly. Legacy does not.\n\nBug: 1003545\nChange-Id: I1510611ff84a99a26bcade74cace2855e022f997\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1830326\nCommit-Queue: Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Ian Kilpatrick \u003cikilpatrick@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702150}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 2f0b747361dc9b66b7dfc9e28d91fd84f346dd49\nwpt-pr: 19383\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-position/position-absolute-replaced-minmax.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e9b74acb717d9d870cc2b892f81f98e3c89a1f4", "parents": ["f4c0bd2e932f61feb4e4cfe6a927337461ceb0cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Philip J\u00e4genstedt \u003cphilip@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1583890 [wpt PR 19303] - Build docs when touching docs/ and select directories in PRs, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nBuild docs when touching docs/ and select directories in PRs (#19303)\n\n* Build docs when modifying docs/ in PRs\n\n* Build docs for resources/ and tools/ too\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 052f1b22f84f373c38b636ee321f84b79fd6f3ec\nwpt-pr: 19303\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/.github/workflows/build-publish-documentation-website.yml", "testing/web-platform/tests/.github/workflows/push-build-publish-documentation-website.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "781fca7115fa0047c653c6fe96336c25680207c3", "parents": ["3e9b74acb717d9d870cc2b892f81f98e3c89a1f4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584504 [wpt PR 19366] - Convert XRSessionClient to new Mojo types, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nConvert XRSessionClient to new Mojo types\n\nThis CL converts XRSessionClient{Ptr, Request} in chrome and blink\nto the new Mojo type, and uses pending_receiver\u003cXRSessionClient\u003e\nin vr_service.mojom.\n\nBug: 955171, 978694\nChange-Id: Ia226a135173cd3e38c3b52a60beaae562ac63d3c\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1828760\nReviewed-by: Kent Tamura \u003ctkent@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Ken Rockot \u003crockot@google.com\u003e\nReviewed-by: Sam McNally \u003csammc@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Brandon Jones \u003cbajones@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Klaus Weidner \u003cklausw@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702221}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: c2eb1ace567d212e6faf0fd0a0f3ba97e46c0af7\nwpt-pr: 19366\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/resources/chromium/webxr-test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55d59c7c78b1735bf927836d608f18fc624ceb4c", "parents": ["781fca7115fa0047c653c6fe96336c25680207c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "jugglinmike \u003cmike@mikepennisi.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585805 [wpt PR 19478] - [encoding] Defer API reference, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[encoding] Defer API reference (#19478)\n\nThis test references the API under test outside the context of a\nsubtest. This produces an uncaught exception in non-conforming\nimplementations. Currently, testharness.js interprets this result as a\nfailing \"single-page test,\" although it will soon be more accurately\nreported as a harness error [1].\n\nUpdate the test to only reference the API from within the body of a\nsubtest.\n\n[1] https://github.com/web-platform-tests/rfcs/blob/master/rfcs/single_test.md\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 4048e00ff8a82125d05e267fbd4c1b317d135a6e\nwpt-pr: 19478\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/encoding/streams/backpressure.any.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e54fa578d6cdf58fb3b35ec52bc83d40699e72a2", "parents": ["55d59c7c78b1735bf927836d608f18fc624ceb4c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585805 [wpt PR 19478] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19478\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/encoding/streams/backpressure.any.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c4418df2ebb61eb531963e353fa2c95b1ca43793", "parents": ["e54fa578d6cdf58fb3b35ec52bc83d40699e72a2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584502 [wpt PR 19365] - Convert XRPresentationClient to new Mojo types, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nConvert XRPresentationClient to new Mojo types\n\nThis CL converts XRPresentationClientPtr in chrome, device and\nblink to the new Mojo type, and uses\npending_receiver\u003cXRPresentationClient\u003e in vr_service.mojom.\n\nBug: 955171, 978694\nChange-Id: I2ea508b31be493653edd2301758855b8c63efc79\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1828724\nReviewed-by: Ken Rockot \u003crockot@google.com\u003e\nReviewed-by: Sam McNally \u003csammc@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Piotr Bialecki \u003cbialpio@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Brandon Jones \u003cbajones@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Klaus Weidner \u003cklausw@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702283}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 7e1e59ff2ad535e088f0d126c3a01fd45b07e5d9\nwpt-pr: 19365\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/resources/chromium/webxr-test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "19f500d63b4bf83263b591d44aeaa97fae48997c", "parents": ["c4418df2ebb61eb531963e353fa2c95b1ca43793"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585766 [wpt PR 19475] - Port background-position-x(y)-interpolation to wpt, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nPort background-position-x(y)-interpolation to wpt\n\nThis CL ports two interpolation tests to wpt.\n\nBug: 900581\nChange-Id: Ib0724e6854b0bf159bd9054730dd7bfb31fd9d10\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1810196\nReviewed-by: Yi Gu \u003cyigu@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702289}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 2612d6db427a6cf148ade7bd2ceff3444f165877\nwpt-pr: 19475\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-backgrounds/animations/background-position-x-interpolation.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-backgrounds/animations/background-position-y-interpolation.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ebe094b29bc2f382f375995c0d9a67e5f26b16ba", "parents": ["19f500d63b4bf83263b591d44aeaa97fae48997c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryosuke Niwa \u003crniwa@webkit.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585809 [wpt PR 19479] - Use static getter to define disabledFeatures, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nshadow-dom: Use static getter to define disabledFeatures (#19479)\n\nThis allows shadow-dom/Element-interface-attachShadow-custom-element.html to run in Safari (it currently fails).\n--\n\nwpt-commits: beca8464a59440d44a41edbba1989e8d6dc2a38e\nwpt-pr: 19479\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/shadow-dom/Element-interface-attachShadow-custom-element.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ece6421f4d6ac88996389ed75ef53004cc4c6ef", "parents": ["ebe094b29bc2f382f375995c0d9a67e5f26b16ba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585809 [wpt PR 19479] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19479\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/shadow-dom/Element-interface-attachShadow-custom-element.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9be020101a35b8094b9a89acce5379fa3739442f", "parents": ["0ece6421f4d6ac88996389ed75ef53004cc4c6ef"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Staphany Park \u003cstaphany@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585871 [wpt PR 19486] - Cookie Store: Add test for cookiechange subscription list., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nCookie Store: Add test for cookiechange subscription list.\n\nBug: 963042\nChange-Id: Ic9fbccdabf8ca49b694b4195e7262d3e80a4be6f\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1836662\nCommit-Queue: Staphany Park \u003cstaphany@chromium.org\u003e\nAuto-Submit: Staphany Park \u003cstaphany@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Victor Costan \u003cpwnall@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702304}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: da8f4e657b845b4f6b828adc2e67a63fcfd840ea\nwpt-pr: 19486\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/cookie-store/serviceworker_cookieStore_subscriptions_reset.sub.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/cookie-store/serviceworker_cookieStore_subscriptions_reset.tentative.https.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c23ecbb2ca7a1a86deb00c84572ed4b9b5793839", "parents": ["9be020101a35b8094b9a89acce5379fa3739442f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585871 [wpt PR 19486] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19486\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/cookie-store/serviceworker_cookieStore_subscriptions_reset.tentative.https.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b26286d8bd026a910c804c5457a3cb7e157db6d", "parents": ["c23ecbb2ca7a1a86deb00c84572ed4b9b5793839"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585142 [wpt PR 19413] - [OT-PW] Fixes crash when drawing patterns, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[OT-PW] Fixes crash when drawing patterns\n\nRight now the PaintWorkletDeferredImage keeps a scoped_refptr to the\nPaintWorkletInput, and during the CreateShader function, the ownership\nof that PaintWorkletInput is given to a PaintImage, which is then used\nto create a PaintShader.\n\nNotice that the CreateShader function can be called multiple times,\nand in this case the PaintWorkletInput is nullptr after the first call.\nAnd then it triggers a crash in PaintShader::MakeImage.\n\nTo fix this, we make the PaintWorkletDeferredImage keeps a PaintImage\nwhich would always own the PaintWorkletInput that is passed to it.\nWhen CreateShader is called, we can use the PaintImage to build the\nshader.\n\nA layout test is added to ensure there is no crash.\n\nBug: 1009450\nChange-Id: I8fa5f45728884fe213176b4f5490329259a19a27\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1831790\nReviewed-by: Stephen McGruer \u003csmcgruer@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Rune Lillesveen \u003cfuthark@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702392}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 66a2fe2ae02b32e910ff091904653e62ec0c9060\nwpt-pr: 19413\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-paint-api/geometry-border-image-005-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-paint-api/geometry-border-image-005.https.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cfd6f7a929454725dd852b546b0fa9a0d264874b", "parents": ["8b26286d8bd026a910c804c5457a3cb7e157db6d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585142 [wpt PR 19413] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19413\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-paint-api/geometry-border-image-005.https.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "19a49bcb64b5dbc9842bbb22b61128532bab24ae", "parents": ["cfd6f7a929454725dd852b546b0fa9a0d264874b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "autofoolip \u003cauto@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585960 [wpt PR 19490] - Update interfaces/webrtc-stats.idl, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate interfaces/webrtc-stats.idl (#19490)\n\nSource: https://github.com/tidoust/reffy-reports/blob/a6313d3/ed/idl/webrtc-stats.idl\nBuild: https://travis-ci.org/tidoust/reffy-reports/builds/593030831\n--\n\nwpt-commits: b3ceebd1a17e0c49635efa55581d4ee47d830e19\nwpt-pr: 19490\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/interfaces/webrtc-stats.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6e74ec4074c1f7b4060ccc960395fcfe588500c0", "parents": ["19a49bcb64b5dbc9842bbb22b61128532bab24ae"], "tags": []}, {"author": "autofoolip \u003cauto@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586066 [wpt PR 19494] - Update interfaces/feature-policy.idl, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate interfaces/feature-policy.idl (#19494)\n\nSource: https://github.com/tidoust/reffy-reports/blob/0e6b3ac/ed/idl/feature-policy.idl\nBuild: https://travis-ci.org/tidoust/reffy-reports/builds/593187538\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 93bf780b41868438e1703453fccef8a0da0a7433\nwpt-pr: 19494\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/interfaces/feature-policy.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "397e9e644e72aa7a726e8a48e1fbe98ac6a8fc19", "parents": ["6e74ec4074c1f7b4060ccc960395fcfe588500c0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586066 [wpt PR 19494] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19494\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/feature-policy/idlharness.window.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c89fc4322bc59463b21569f8c909110a6aaf8fe8", "parents": ["397e9e644e72aa7a726e8a48e1fbe98ac6a8fc19"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ian Kilpatrick \u003cikilpatrick@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1583577 [wpt PR 19257] - [LayoutNG] Clear layout results when the layout wasn't successful., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Clear layout results when the layout wasn't successful.\n\nToday we can end up in a state where the layout result cache for a\nLayoutBox contains a fragment tree which doesn't match the layout tree\nstate.\n\nThis occurs when we \"abort\" layout, i.e.\n1) during the first pass children are positioned at a particular offset\n2) a parent aborts layout due to resolving a BFC offset\n3) the parent hits the layout result cache which has children at a\n   different offset\n\nBug: 1003558\nChange-Id: Iabc5dfefd74c517222ec435cea376ad000a0372f\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1821674\nReviewed-by: Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Ian Kilpatrick \u003cikilpatrick@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702507}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: eac401e3df87f17e49b38ec2f935fd1177139e23\nwpt-pr: 19257\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/floats/adjoining-floats-dynamic.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b798e8d5219d28f23ca28d0b5977e00510d55907", "parents": ["c89fc4322bc59463b21569f8c909110a6aaf8fe8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585889 [wpt PR 19487] - [LayoutNG] Fix clusterfuzz crash, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Fix clusterfuzz crash\n\nUsing empty Optional\u003cMinMax\u003e to indicate that MinMax value\nshould not matter caused trouble with ng_length_utils\nResolveInlineLengthInternal, when max-width was fit-content.\n\nUse MinMax(0, LayoutUnitMax) to indicate intrinsic size does\nnot matter instead. It accomplishes the same goal, computed\nsize does not get clamped by intrinsic.\n\nI've also tested running it with width:max-content out of\nfear that we might end up with too wide OOF, but that did\nnot happen.\n\nBug: 1010798\nChange-Id: Ife11b3d9637be91cc0648b7f8485af51f07108bb\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1837118\nCommit-Queue: Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e\nAuto-Submit: Aleks Totic \u003catotic@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702525}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: baf914481d76b25d7d054a23564d5b5418dd9f8b\nwpt-pr: 19487\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-position/position-absolute-replaced-minmax.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39986b1b8895b2e6067b1cbc931e2c3f43f682fb", "parents": ["b798e8d5219d28f23ca28d0b5977e00510d55907"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586004 [wpt PR 19491] - [LayoutNG] Fix bidi reordering of lines with empty inline boxes, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Fix bidi reordering of lines with empty inline boxes\n\nThis patch fixes bidi reordering sometimes confused by empty\ninline boxes.\n\nThese items do not have resolved bidi levels. Before this\npatch, |NGInlineLayoutAlgorithm| reordered ignoring such\nitems. This patch changes it to assign bidi levels to such\nitems by copying from adjacent items and let reordering to\nhandle them.\n\nBug: 1010662, 1010641, 998872\nChange-Id: I5d074143970b83b64bddbb83cd03b17551e3f521\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1837435\nReviewed-by: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e\nAuto-Submit: Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702526}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 7cbaaf651d784a5c90fde0ff0b1aa6c029c5f2f3\nwpt-pr: 19491\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/text/bidi-span-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/text/bidi-span-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/text/bidi-span-002-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/text/bidi-span-002.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f383200b32df78c6b67d6e0be04766d5f3eb8c8", "parents": ["39986b1b8895b2e6067b1cbc931e2c3f43f682fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584484 [wpt PR 19363] - Convert VRService client to use BrowserInterfaceBroker, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nConvert VRService client to use BrowserInterfaceBroker\n\nThis change converts VRService mojom interface client in blink\nto use BrowserInterfaceBroker, and converts VRService{Ptr, Request}\nin chrome, content and blink to the new Mojo type.\n\nBug: 936482, 955171, 978694\nChange-Id: Ib2d982ea3402c570c825e2b55d7aec2c77b2d8c6\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1828717\nCommit-Queue: Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e\nReviewed-by: Oksana Zhuravlova \u003coksamyt@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Kent Tamura \u003ctkent@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Kinuko Yasuda \u003ckinuko@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Klaus Weidner \u003cklausw@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702732}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: c5b16519bfdc8e9c849a30f93bd26ab0dc05a2b2\nwpt-pr: 19363\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/resources/chromium/webxr-test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "64de5bf5d63e7e759b4cc562f9902bf8438844cc", "parents": ["0f383200b32df78c6b67d6e0be04766d5f3eb8c8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Soromou \u003cfosoromo@microsoft.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586084 [wpt PR 19496] - Service Worker: Fetch event added asynchronously doesn't throw., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nService Worker: Fetch event added asynchronously doesn't throw.\n\nBased on the spec (https://github.com/whatwg/dom/pull/653),\naddEventListener after the first evaluation of the Service\nworker script should not throw.\n\nChange-Id: I46af276a67e021cf277a98195bf5c04583ad0b0a\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1838376\nReviewed-by: Matt Falkenhagen \u003cfalken@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Daniel Soromou \u003cfosoromo@microsoft.com\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702753}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 42efecfdb246ea0f22b5a82f5c13659894de3d72\nwpt-pr: 19496\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/fetch-event-add-async.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/resources/fetch-event-add-async-worker.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "85284299266e6cd046f12ed3a588f973b6013590", "parents": ["64de5bf5d63e7e759b4cc562f9902bf8438844cc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yuta Kasai \u003cyutakasai@google.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1583474 [wpt PR 19246] - Service worker: Add self.serviceWorker to ServiceWorkerGlobalScope, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nService worker: Add self.serviceWorker to ServiceWorkerGlobalScope\n\n- In the previous code, the expiration time was set to null\n  so that remaining_timeout() was negative during initial script\n  evaluation so that calling self.serviceWorker.postMessage() would fail.\n  This CL sets max_request_expiration_time properly\n  in ServiceWorkerVersion::StartWorkerInternal().\n- Add and fix unittests about expiration time.\n- Fix the expected.txt properly.\n- In spec, service worker's initial state should be parsed.\n  https://w3c.github.io/ServiceWorker/#service-worker-concept\n\nLink to the Chrome Platform Status: https://chromestatus.com/feature/6678900060979200\n\nBug: 977496\nChange-Id: I4f8368e165fb84304b49519ed43d7b21d5ec756d\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1819091\nReviewed-by: Kinuko Yasuda \u003ckinuko@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Kent Tamura \u003ctkent@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Matt Falkenhagen \u003cfalken@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Makoto Shimazu \u003cshimazu@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Yuta Kasai \u003cyutakasai@google.com\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702788}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 8561e5223c46c4a47f1fef1fe0b2b18ea7341d19\nwpt-pr: 19246\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/global-serviceworker.https.any.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "95e1f1809a298d771a4b51edf6c4dd782adc70ce", "parents": ["85284299266e6cd046f12ed3a588f973b6013590"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eric Willigers \u003cewilligers@users.noreply.github.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584386 [wpt PR 19346] - [css-masking] Parse mask shorthand, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[css-masking] Parse mask shorthand (#19346)\n\nTest parsing of the components of the 'mask' shorthand.\n\nhttps://www.w3.org/TR/css-masking-1/#the-mask\n\nFirefox rejects \"none margin-box\", otherwise tests pass in Firefox.\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 04c6f30bcca263bb2e86e94125f2aaa36e5b2e7b\nwpt-pr: 19346\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-masking/parsing/mask-invalid.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-masking/parsing/mask-valid.sub.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1792e200cbca309b00b84be330232adf0b750d9c", "parents": ["95e1f1809a298d771a4b51edf6c4dd782adc70ce"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584386 [wpt PR 19346] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19346\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-masking/parsing/mask-valid.sub.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c3dd4ffdfada613348c898cd5585dfdd387d8e10", "parents": ["1792e200cbca309b00b84be330232adf0b750d9c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rayan Kanso \u003crayankans@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585717 [wpt PR 19469] - [Contacts] Update implementation to match spec changes., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[Contacts] Update implementation to match spec changes.\n\n- Expose the `address` property and place it behind a flag.\n- Add & implement the getProperties method.\n\nChange-Id: If9bbebde6b8d076fd48b0b8a3584181e40adc1d4\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1835621\nReviewed-by: Stephen White \u003csenorblanco@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Peter Beverloo \u003cpeter@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Rayan Kanso \u003crayankans@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#702810}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: a18270ee5ec0f752d7116ce14204bff3e6b7ec17\nwpt-pr: 19469\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/contacts/contacts-select.https.window.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ac32c3759b429c8259a100e37353862f4312e590", "parents": ["c3dd4ffdfada613348c898cd5585dfdd387d8e10"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585717 [wpt PR 19469] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19469\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/contacts/contacts-select.https.window.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "158cfff45561db0d1401b8a7f6dd5ea503369b0a", "parents": ["ac32c3759b429c8259a100e37353862f4312e590"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Carlos Alberto Lopez Perez \u003cclopez@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586930 [wpt PR 19466] - Add webkitgtk_minibrowser runs to taskcluster daily., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nAdd webkitgtk_minibrowser runs to taskcluster daily. (#19466)\n\nThis is testing with the stable channel for now,\nbeta or nightly channels may be integrated later.\n\nIt uses a different docker image on taskcluster that\nis currently configured with the last stable version\nof WebKitGTK with experimental features enabled.\n\nWhen the test start in taskcluster the browser will be installed\nfrom the required channel.\n\nEnable at run-time on webkitgtk_minibrowser some\nfeatures that are disabled by default.\n\nEnsure also that the required --host=127.0.0.1\nargument when running in docker is automatically\npassed to the webdriver by the wpt runner.\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 9f0aff8885b01a38dcce738c02c58bd66300a25d\nwpt-pr: 19466\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/.taskcluster.yml", "testing/web-platform/tests/docs/running-tests/webkitgtk_minibrowser.md", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/ci/run_tc.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/docker/Dockerfile.webkitgtk", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/docker/README.md", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/browsers/base.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/browsers/epiphany.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/browsers/webkitgtk_minibrowser.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a4f22c5e43d7755b704813243f54b73953fdfaa9", "parents": ["158cfff45561db0d1401b8a7f6dd5ea503369b0a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586930 - [wpt-sync] Update web-platform-tests to 9f0aff8885b01a38dcce738c02c58bd66300a25d, a=testonly\n\nMANUAL PUSH: wpt sync bot\n\nwpt-head: 9f0aff8885b01a38dcce738c02c58bd66300a25d\nwpt-type: landing\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/2dcontext/drawing-text-to-the-canvas/2d.text.draw.fontface.notinpage.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/acid/acid2/reftest.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/acid/acid3/test.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/compat/webkit-radial-gradient-radii.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/content-security-policy/inheritance/unsandboxed-blob-scheme.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/content-security-policy/navigate-to/form-redirected-blocked.sub.html.ini", "test