de5442b23fe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jorg K \u003cjorgk@jorgk.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1588979 - Add missing QI in LoginManager.jsm and fix version check in LoginStore.jsm. r=MattN\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49444", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/LoginManager.jsm", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/LoginStore.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "024c8c2242d608d7c928948f15093f198b9270ae", "parents": ["520d76b5e3bcfc8ae2256acd4ae4ec0b75ac75a2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "shindli \u003cshindli@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 00b56e289d2e (bug 1585769) for causing perma bc failures in toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/tests/browser_thirdPartyIframe.js CLOSED TREE", "files": ["toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/tests/browser.ini", "toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/tests/browser_thirdPartyIframe.js", "toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/tests/head.js", "toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/tests/test-page-with-iframe.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a31cb7d5f3ba3cfc9b0d8376e31f4fb96a817a10", "parents": ["024c8c2242d608d7c928948f15093f198b9270ae"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1580894 - Enable subgrid by default.  r=dholbert\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D47344", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2c962324e4a04279bbbfdc1d53e2fee8ce66c1cf", "parents": ["a31cb7d5f3ba3cfc9b0d8376e31f4fb96a817a10"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399866 - Trigger global's read barrier in js::NewProxyObject r=sfink\n\nWhen remapping wrappers the embedding can call this to create a new proxy object while in a realm whose global is gray. This breaks the JS API invariants and can cause black to gray GC edges to be creaated. Fix this by triggering the global's read barrier here.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49430", "files": ["js/src/proxy/Proxy.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cec21bd2065865bc33b84e3c6b65e7a65ef3b6ea", "parents": ["2c962324e4a04279bbbfdc1d53e2fee8ce66c1cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399866 - Add assertions that we don't create black to gray edges from ObjectGroups to global objects r=sfink\n\nNot a fix. This patch adds some assertions that we don't ever set the realm of an ObjectGroup such that it points to a gray global object. We have these asserts already for other types of edge but this one is indirect because we store a pointer to the Realm, and get the global from that.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49302", "files": ["js/src/gc/GC.cpp", "js/src/vm/ObjectGroup.cpp", "js/src/vm/ObjectGroup.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f2ab1f1dc330bbc931935d1167be2850a773a62", "parents": ["cec21bd2065865bc33b84e3c6b65e7a65ef3b6ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586262 - Ensure run-task logs very long task output lines; r=dustin\n\nCheck the return code of write() to determine if the output line has actually been written completely; if not, write the remainder.\n\nTests suggest that incomplete writes are possible when the buffer exceeds a few thousand bytes. Very long log lines are unusual but this is important for cases like reftest failures where an encoded screenshot is dumped to the log.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D48218", "files": ["taskcluster/scripts/run-task"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bcfc1146667cd293c6f3cdd819fa0a82515585b7", "parents": ["0f2ab1f1dc330bbc931935d1167be2850a773a62"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emma Malysz \u003cemalysz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1588918, rename .xul test files in accessible/ to .xhtml r=surkov\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49355", "files": [".eslintrc.js", "accessible/tests/browser/states/browser.ini", "accessible/tests/browser/states/browser_deck_has_out_of_process_iframe.js", "accessible/tests/browser/states/test_deck_has_out_of_process_iframe.xhtml", "accessible/tests/browser/states/test_deck_has_out_of_process_iframe.xul", "accessible/tests/crashtests/471493.xhtml", "accessible/tests/crashtests/471493.xul", "accessible/tests/crashtests/crashtests.list", "accessible/tests/crashtests/last_test_to_unload_testsuite.xhtml", "accessible/tests/crashtests/last_test_to_unload_testsuite.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/a11y.ini", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_general.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_general.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_keys_menu.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_keys_menu.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_tree.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_tree.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_treegrid.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/actions/test_treegrid.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/attributes/a11y.ini", "accessible/tests/mochitest/attributes/test_obj_css.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/attributes/test_obj_css.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/attributes/test_obj_group.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/attributes/test_obj_group.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/attributes/test_obj_group_tree.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/attributes/test_obj_group_tree.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/elm/a11y.ini", "accessible/tests/mochitest/elm/test_listbox.xhtml", "accessible/tests/mochitest/elm/test_listbox.xul", "accessible/tests/mochitest/events/a11y.ini", "accessible/tests/mochitest/events/test_focus_autocomplete.xhtml", "accessible/te