\u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1583579 [wpt PR 19258] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19258\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/measure-memory/measure-memory.tentative.any.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a569a8b0a15cdf400a0e69c13a6835ddcf73f7f", "parents": ["6a22608f94ef200c952943739cd16ed6a9a2f923"], "tags": []}, {"author": "jugglinmike \u003cmike@mikepennisi.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585418 [wpt PR 19449] - [testharness.js] Implement `single_test` option, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[testharness.js] Implement `single_test` option (#19449)\n\nThe behavior and deployment schedule of this option was defined via the\nfollowing web-platform-tests RFC:\nhttps://github.com/web-platform-tests/rfcs/blob/master/rfcs/single_test.md\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 819a234d3dd3a8400d57fa449123cbb01bb33226\nwpt-pr: 19449\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/docs/writing-tests/testharness-api.md", "testing/web-platform/tests/resources/test/nested-testharness.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/resources/test/tests/unit/single_test.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/resources/testharness.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "329d93800a86b390d14fe2b389b461974390251b", "parents": ["3a569a8b0a15cdf400a0e69c13a6835ddcf73f7f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Simon Pieters \u003czcorpan@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586742 [wpt PR 19548] - [docs] Add documentation for common/, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[docs] Add documentation for common/\n\nPart of #17913.\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 2ae499f937640068f33d547423bfeb8c3dbf5295\nwpt-pr: 19548\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/common/README.md", "testing/web-platform/tests/common/security-features/README.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5f0b43a83a0c7c11286e149f65e7be63a0cdeea7", "parents": ["329d93800a86b390d14fe2b389b461974390251b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Stephen McGruer \u003csmcgruer@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586876 [wpt PR 19554] - [web-animations-1] Fix typo in test, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[web-animations-1] Fix typo in test (#19554)\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: d9a9f2970d628001ff100548a6fd1ee750802893\nwpt-pr: 19554\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/web-animations/animation-model/animation-types/property-types.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90449bec1de2cdf9733993b00810b4b5faf31d91", "parents": ["5f0b43a83a0c7c11286e149f65e7be63a0cdeea7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586876 [wpt PR 19554] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19554\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/web-animations/animation-model/animation-types/interpolation-per-property.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8d60d0d97784c822f04a2366085e2e2f4448d582", "parents": ["90449bec1de2cdf9733993b00810b4b5faf31d91"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Asa Kusuma \u003casa.kusuma@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582047 [wpt PR 19132] - Clear-Site-Data: clients uncontrolled by service workers, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nClear-Site-Data: clients uncontrolled by service workers after storage directive (#19132)\n\nAdds a failing test, asserting that pages actively controlled by a service worker become uncontrolled after the Clear-Site-Data storage directive.\n\nWe agreed on this behavior in a spec issue and confirmed the need for this test at the TPAC Service Workers F2F.\n\nhttps://github.com/w3c/ServiceWorker/issues/614\nF2F notes: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1_Qfw5m3BJEaL1xIzTJd41HXjgJ9gq7mroBDXqSJIzic/edit\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 8be01b6e0d191a641f45ad59e83718155775921d\nwpt-pr: 19132\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/clear-site-data/storage.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/clear-site-data/support/controlled-endpoint.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/clear-site-data/support/page_using_service_worker.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/clear-site-data/support/service_worker.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/clear-site-data/support/test_utils.sub.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b899d0a8c9d3cff2b26f20ca5235418b65447ba", "parents": ["8d60d0d97784c822f04a2366085e2e2f4448d582"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastiaan Nijland \u003c19267753+SebastiaanNijland@users.noreply.github.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586773 [wpt PR 19551] - docs: update the readme link for running https tests, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\ndocs: update the readme link for running https tests (#19551)\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: f951c9d8c79e03d656d2427fa5f3e0dce4c6efe5\nwpt-pr: 19551\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/README.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6f50b783174f4d403758e034221a9fef67097002", "parents": ["8b899d0a8c9d3cff2b26f20ca5235418b65447ba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eric Willigers \u003cericwilligers@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586242 [wpt PR 19509] - CSS: Test shorthand expansion, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nCSS: Test shorthand expansion\n\nWhen a longhand value is omitted, the longhand should have the specific\ninitial value for the shorthand, not 'initial'.\n\nBug: 501673, 772772\nChange-Id: I0986013e6785852861b79926dd0696314c758ff7\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1839934\nReviewed-by: Rune Lillesveen \u003cfuthark@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Eric Willigers \u003cericwilligers@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703528}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: bb904ca75f9da8d5392b4ed670f8033ecfd361f3\nwpt-pr: 19509\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-grid/parsing/grid-shorthand.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-multicol/parsing/column-rule-shorthand.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/motion/parsing/offset-shorthand.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/support/shorthand-testcommon.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b548a90b6493f1e2c15ad5fa390f69c945aaaddf", "parents": ["6f50b783174f4d403758e034221a9fef67097002"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586242 [wpt PR 19509] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19509\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/motion/parsing/offset-shorthand.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e9829f679b4be7589100c2842642615b2b422a99", "parents": ["b548a90b6493f1e2c15ad5fa390f69c945aaaddf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Josh Matthews \u003cjosh@joshmatthews.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586424 [wpt PR 19529] - Allow using CORS filtered image responses as WebGL textures, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nEnsure image cache keys on element CORS status.\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 62ee04cd0ea0765975f82fb1b130990df9ecf8e3\nwpt-pr: 19529\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/2dcontext/drawing-images-to-the-canvas/drawimage_crossorigin.sub.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "912fb841454b8d33b89dadcb5547bde4305d2ddf", "parents": ["e9829f679b4be7589100c2842642615b2b422a99"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroki Nakagawa \u003cnhiroki@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585564 [wpt PR 19462] - Worklet: Reject addModule() with script's error to rethrow if available, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nWorklet: Reject addModule() with script's error to rethrow if available\n\nThis CL makes Worklet#addModule() fail with a more specific error object\ncompared to before.\n\nBefore this change, Worklet::addModule() was rejected with AbortError regardless\nof an actual error reason, and that made it difficult for developers to debug\nworklets. This behavior was defined in the Worklets spec, but it was changed\nrecently (see the links below).\n\nAfter this change, Worklet::addModule() is rejected with script's error to\nrethrow when it is available as the new spec defines.\n\nSpec changes:\n- https://github.com/w3c/css-houdini-drafts/pull/958\n- https://github.com/w3c/css-houdini-drafts/pull/967\n\nChromestatus:\n- https://www.chromestatus.com/feature/5116796497559552\n\nBug: 782066\nChange-Id: Iabd30eff28ed1bffed9219898649a89b8abebbb2\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1258785\nReviewed-by: Kouhei Ueno \u003ckouhei@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Hiroshige Hayashizaki \u003chiroshige@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Hiroki Nakagawa \u003cnhiroki@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703606}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 162858b9961ab26dbbe27e07bea2d6e6d10702df\nwpt-pr: 19462\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/worklets/resources/import-tests.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "be5a525dc0ae96f3bca68b403b22e4bb3bfc56b0", "parents": ["912fb841454b8d33b89dadcb5547bde4305d2ddf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585564 [wpt PR 19462] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19462\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/worklets/audio-worklet-import.https.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "26b70e39b259fa43748a034a3c04ac1673fd1c43", "parents": ["be5a525dc0ae96f3bca68b403b22e4bb3bfc56b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Adam Rice \u003cricea@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586981 [wpt PR 19563] - Turn on backpressure for blink::WebSocketStream sooner, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nTurn on backpressure for blink::WebSocketStream sooner\n\nApply backpressure to blink::WebSocketChannel before the WebSocketStream\nhandshake starts, rather than after it completes. This avoids a race\ncondition where more of the first message is read than should be.\n\nAlso fix flakiness in the\nexternal/wpt/websockets/stream-tentative/backpressure-receive.any.js by\ndoubling the size of message used.\n\nBUG=1002780\n\nChange-Id: I915c71a4b81b95375b7c4c584f7782d5336cba85\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1844911\nReviewed-by: Yutaka Hirano \u003cyhirano@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Adam Rice \u003cricea@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703610}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: b3807b6ffe70db1bcaa28cf8b5aa8c6da025b5fa\nwpt-pr: 19563\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/websockets/handlers/send-backpressure_wsh.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/websockets/stream-tentative/backpressure-receive.any.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cdc6a42731a9acf2745cc095351108de24b3ccca", "parents": ["26b70e39b259fa43748a034a3c04ac1673fd1c43"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586758 [wpt PR 19549] - Convert WebUsbService client to use BrowserInterfaceBroker, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nConvert WebUsbService client to use BrowserInterfaceBroker\n\nThis change converts WebUsbService mojom interface client in blink\nto use BrowserInterfaceBroker.\n\nBug: 936482\nChange-Id: I03f8d6b061eed920ffd68305702f73fff66fe871\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1844005\nReviewed-by: Oksana Zhuravlova \u003coksamyt@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Kent Tamura \u003ctkent@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Kinuko Yasuda \u003ckinuko@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Miyoung Shin \u003cmyid.shin@igalia.com\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703611}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 965481541d2f8e6b4b347a8048031985a1fa8e27\nwpt-pr: 19549\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/resources/chromium/webusb-child-test.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/resources/chromium/webusb-test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ae5c60e71f94f2de3a7ad55e982c8e2c7e8fd08b", "parents": ["cdc6a42731a9acf2745cc095351108de24b3ccca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cathie Chen \u003ccathiechen@igalia.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587024 [wpt PR 19566] - The size of OverflowClipRect is negative, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nThe size of OverflowClipRect is negative\n\nWhen scrollbar wider than the scrollar, the size of OverflowClipRect\nis negative which will affect the value of scroll offset. This patch\nmake the size non-negative.\n\nBug: 987566\nChange-Id: I7fa80e4a17bc48303713a1a191230d0b3e7d0dd5\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1840492\nCommit-Queue: cathie chen \u003ccathiechen@igalia.com\u003e\nReviewed-by: David Bokan \u003cbokan@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703662}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 6e56893172d7f8bc833e9859c97ad5e52e9eb937\nwpt-pr: 19566\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/cssom-view/scrollLeft-of-scroller-with-wider-scrollbar.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65016d3b9885fe7e43f4035837c73071e40e548b", "parents": ["ae5c60e71f94f2de3a7ad55e982c8e2c7e8fd08b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Philip J\u00e4genstedt \u003cphilip@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587048 [wpt PR 19568] - Use `zstd --no-progress` in manifest_build.py, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUse `zstd --no-progress` in manifest_build.py (#19568)\n\ngzip and bzip2 are silent by default.\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 1dd29f0138509c085c01df7ec3214231d28853b8\nwpt-pr: 19568\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/ci/manifest_build.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "be5728d38c51dee3ab5dc848b20313c6d49c5bbe", "parents": ["65016d3b9885fe7e43f4035837c73071e40e548b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Philip J\u00e4genstedt \u003cphilip@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587032 [wpt PR 19567] - [GitHub Actions] shorten names of workflow files and names, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[GitHub Actions] shorten names of workflow files and names\n\nWith this, instead of checks named like this:\n - \"Build & Release Manifest / manifest-build-and-tag\"\n - \"Build & Publish Documentation Website / website-build-and-publish\"\n\nThe checks will installed be named like this:\n - \"manifest / build-and-tag\"\n - \"documentation / build-and-publish\"\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: ff3e2b5734b8ec13fe2f8b9aff138c5578f373f8\nwpt-pr: 19567\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/.github/workflows/build-publish-documentation-website.yml", "testing/web-platform/tests/.github/workflows/documentation.yml", "testing/web-platform/tests/.github/workflows/manifest.yml", "testing/web-platform/tests/.github/workflows/push-build-release-manifest.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f576c0cc94ee32b684867f6ed47fad2f0486a3c", "parents": ["be5728d38c51dee3ab5dc848b20313c6d49c5bbe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Philip J\u00e4genstedt \u003cphilip@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587100 [wpt PR 19571] - Revert \"Use `zstd --no-progress` in manifest_build.py\", a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nRevert \"Use `zstd --no-progress` in manifest_build.py\" (#19571)\n\nThis reverts commit 1dd29f0138509c085c01df7ec3214231d28853b8.\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 7771c4cda2aa570d0bb54d6b7b28e804f0e85e2e\nwpt-pr: 19571\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/ci/manifest_build.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d563d33b72477fc9fa36ce51cc99d0b280f4d089", "parents": ["1f576c0cc94ee32b684867f6ed47fad2f0486a3c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Simon Pieters \u003czcorpan@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587081 [wpt PR 19569] - Rename lone .headers file, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nRename lone .headers file (#19569)\n\nThe corresponding file was renamed in 0bfaa837553a7b66b84b207e702b6b403ad6d990\n--\n\nwpt-commits: cdee611d3fe90fd05c3da262b81cf6b7c0414b9a\nwpt-pr: 19569\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/common/css-paint-tests.js.headers", "testing/web-platform/tests/common/worklet-reftest.js.headers"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7ee185e9892bd382eb9fceacc6fcde2caf56b288", "parents": ["d563d33b72477fc9fa36ce51cc99d0b280f4d089"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586356 [wpt PR 19524] - Port float-interpolation.html to wpt, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nPort float-interpolation.html to wpt\n\nBug: 900581\nChange-Id: Ide1ea499203b960fe59faeecda1a273a0689477c\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1841412\nReviewed-by: Yi Gu \u003cyigu@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Xida Chen \u003cxidachen@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703692}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 7a7a826cd32459b449cc92fba7135ce9039aeb6f\nwpt-pr: 19524\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-logical/animations/float-interpolation.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1e5206a7fea8d9af069ad76fb327452ede68b44", "parents": ["7ee185e9892bd382eb9fceacc6fcde2caf56b288"], "tags": []}, {"author": "pyup-bot \u003cgithub-bot@pyup.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584248 [wpt PR 19327] - Update mypy to 0.730, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate mypy from 0.720 to 0.730\n--\nfixup! Update mypy from 0.720 to 0.730\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: d7789eace2c576625633a913cf5f835aae68238e, 3982e1b6a11e163be4469598421b0cbcf6ecab82\nwpt-pr: 19327\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/XMLParser.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/item.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/requirements_mypy.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f96ab9669e37093602173b83bda5954fd744812", "parents": ["b1e5206a7fea8d9af069ad76fb327452ede68b44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "pyup-bot \u003cgithub-bot@pyup.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585476 [wpt PR 19457] - Update pillow to 6.2.0, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate pillow from 6.1.0 to 6.2.0\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 016aca0f8606b21284161f2772c461e521ce253b\nwpt-pr: 19457\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/requirements.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "083c63574c2bc83f84e1949eb9fdbf1fef2017fb", "parents": ["8f96ab9669e37093602173b83bda5954fd744812"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586651 [wpt PR 19541] - [LayoutNG] Fix line breaking when `font-size: 0`, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Fix line breaking when `font-size: 0`\n\nThis patch fixes line breaking when break opportunities have\n`font-size: 0`.\n\n`font-size: 0` makes all characters at position 0. This\nconfuses when |NGLineBreaker| needs to rewind, and tries to\nfind the break opportunity before the current one.\n\nThis patch fixes it by using |PreviousBreakOpportunity| in\nsuch case.\n\nBug: 1006127\nChange-Id: I449d6f8aaba4deccd458c5e077920b1a8bf79305\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1843991\nReviewed-by: Yoshifumi Inoue \u003cyosin@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703753}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 7fbe6fe5fe834bf28d9171bf92d90287186020e8\nwpt-pr: 19541\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/linebox/line-breaking-font-size-zero-001-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/linebox/line-breaking-font-size-zero-001.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c276749f30a6e5eb8eea53aa5e07a9c154331b03", "parents": ["083c63574c2bc83f84e1949eb9fdbf1fef2017fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olivier Yiptong \u003coyiptong@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586873 [wpt PR 19553] - [Native File System] getFile() returns a File sized correctly, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[Native File System] getFile() returns a File sized correctly\n\nThe getFile() method on NativeFileSystemFileHandleImpl returned a File\nthat wasn't sized correctly. This caused issues when trying to use\nmethods on the File object that would use the bounds to do operations.\n\nBUG=1011179\n\nChange-Id: If900ac39be6b7bfc9d693680aa5d20b6b9c926d8\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1845998\nCommit-Queue: Olivier Yiptong \u003coyiptong@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Marijn Kruisselbrink \u003cmek@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703764}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: eb2527b61be8bfcf0916faa56c47624c90d32bd2\nwpt-pr: 19553\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/native-file-system/native_FileSystemFileHandle-getFile.tentative.https.manual.window.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/native-file-system/sandboxed_FileSystemFileHandle-getFile.tentative.https.any.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/native-file-system/script-tests/FileSystemFileHandle-getFile.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83ed9216cc3bf6fa6eeff59a4eabcb775a5c07bd", "parents": ["c276749f30a6e5eb8eea53aa5e07a9c154331b03"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586873 [wpt PR 19553] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19553\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/native-file-system/native_FileSystemFileHandle-getFile.tentative.https.manual.window.js.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/native-file-system/sandboxed_FileSystemFileHandle-getFile.tentative.https.any.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0766966963d66b48b14f48a90eed5bee29ab740a", "parents": ["83ed9216cc3bf6fa6eeff59a4eabcb775a5c07bd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fredrik S\u00f6derquist \u003cfs@opera.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586263 [wpt PR 19511] - Add some tests for triggering SMIL events via syncbases, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nAdd some tests for triggering SMIL events via syncbases\n\nTests a new begin/end being added by a syncbase, and the corresponding\n'end' event being fired.\n\nBug: 998526\nChange-Id: Ie40f196d4ef2c5fb6b65fced80890a965415cace\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1840692\nCommit-Queue: Stephen Chenney \u003cschenney@chromium.org\u003e\nAuto-Submit: Fredrik S\u00f6derquist \u003cfs@opera.com\u003e\nReviewed-by: Stephen Chenney \u003cschenney@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703778}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: ef62c8fa7b2078d3cbe0e2364573b6e00a72f7d2\nwpt-pr: 19511\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/svg/animations/dependent-begin-on-syncbase.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/svg/animations/dependent-end-on-syncbase.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "09f9e03750fbf625b86626e5704419502178c5d9", "parents": ["0766966963d66b48b14f48a90eed5bee29ab740a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lan Wei \u003clanwei@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586894 [wpt PR 19555] - Change key from \"Ctrl\" to \"Shift\" in actionsWithKeyPressed.html, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nChange key from \"Ctrl\" to \"Shift\" in actionsWithKeyPressed.html\n\nIn this test, we want to test that testdriver Action API supports key\nand mouse action interactions. Clicking with \"Ctrl\" key pressed on Mac\ncauses a context menu open, which fails itself and prevents a\nsubsequent test from running. We can use other keys such as \"Shift\"\nor \"Alt\", which do not open any context menu.\n\nChange-Id: Id9b48440306eeddbd97114bc1ac0f4c9c3c012fc\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1845994\nCommit-Queue: Lan Wei \u003clanwei@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Luke Z \u003clpz@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703792}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: de83b0a0759656d93b536457791bb601c5b7424a\nwpt-pr: 19555\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/infrastructure/metadata/infrastructure/testdriver/actions/actionsWithKeyPressed.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/infrastructure/testdriver/actions/actionsWithKeyPressed.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "442e39d9f96decea6c4510f3aa5b5e238a38e684", "parents": ["09f9e03750fbf625b86626e5704419502178c5d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587134 [wpt PR 19574] - [LayoutNG] Fix font-orientation segmentation, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\n[LayoutNG] Fix font-orientation segmentation\n\nWhen there are no script segments (i.e., all the text is in\nsingle script) and in vertical flow, we create a single\nsegment and split it at the font-orientation boundaries.\n\nThis patch fixes to create the single segment from the first\ntext item, not from the first item. If it is created from the\nfirst item and the first item is not a text item, we may give\nincorrect script and/or font-orientation to HarfBuzz.\n\nBug: 1006154\nChange-Id: I5ea87920f8cbc76cdc13fe25611f7a7a34284813\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1847697\nReviewed-by: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Ian Kilpatrick \u003cikilpatrick@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Emil A Eklund \u003ceae@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Koji Ishii \u003ckojii@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703803}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 4cd56bbc0f6a79a08342e35cbbcfb7e9b700214e\nwpt-pr: 19574\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-writing-modes/mongolian-span-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-writing-modes/reference/mongolian-span-001-ref.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "41d2f4d36b66e25ffdb38b4dc9d77e662fd5d98a", "parents": ["442e39d9f96decea6c4510f3aa5b5e238a38e684"], "tags": []}, {"author": "autofoolip \u003cauto@foolip.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587167 [wpt PR 19575] - Update interfaces/permissions.idl, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUpdate interfaces/permissions.idl (#19575)\n\nSource: https://github.com/tidoust/reffy-reports/blob/6fdf484/ed/idl/permissions.idl\nBuild: https://travis-ci.org/tidoust/reffy-reports/builds/595256477\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 39e9b0311de40fff48c9486bba611f922e2bf28a\nwpt-pr: 19575\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/interfaces/permissions.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d2ff925652e2f83a741fe3617f9f0043bfea1dcf", "parents": ["41d2f4d36b66e25ffdb38b4dc9d77e662fd5d98a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lan Wei \u003clanwei@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586341 [wpt PR 19522] - Use testdriver Action API to automate wpt tests with two touch fingers, a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nUse testdriver Action API to automate wpt tests with two touch fingers\n\nUse testdriver Action API to automate wpt tests with two touch fingers,\npointerevent_touch-action_two-finger_interaction.html.\n\nBug: 606367\nChange-Id: Ia5a0977b3bda9c506dae99c7bfe500fe2a887cad\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1839017\nReviewed-by: Navid Zolghadr \u003cnzolghadr@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: Lan Wei \u003clanwei@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703867}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 583fb12c61bca2dfd94ba12469d0c1a97f6883a4\nwpt-pr: 19522\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/pointerevents/compat/pointerevent_touch-action_two-finger_interaction-manual.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/pointerevents/compat/pointerevent_touch-action_two-finger_interaction.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e7ed7c0c7d6f51f66697850cf02f787fa577f366", "parents": ["d2ff925652e2f83a741fe3617f9f0043bfea1dcf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1586341 [wpt PR 19522] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19522\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/pointerevents/compat/pointerevent_touch-action_two-finger_interaction.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1de6caa2ec6e26a346752578c1ecc2966f195972", "parents": ["e7ed7c0c7d6f51f66697850cf02f787fa577f366"], "tags": []}, {"author": "John Chen \u003cjohnchen@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584612 [wpt PR 19377] - Reland \"[ChromeDriver] Stop using --ignore-certificate-errors\", a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nReland \"[ChromeDriver] Stop using --ignore-certificate-errors\"\n\nThis is a reland of 8f486945b4c91f67b76e02bfd8c39b0a9cf08089\n\nOriginal change's description:\n\u003e [ChromeDriver] Stop using --ignore-certificate-errors\n\u003e\n\u003e ChromeDriver was passing --ignore-certificate-errors switch to Chrome,\n\u003e regardless of whether user wants to ignore certificate errors or not.\n\u003e Fixing by stop passing this flag to Chrome, and relying on using\n\u003e Security.setIgnoreCertificateErrors command when user wants to ignore\n\u003e certificate errors.\n\u003e\n\u003e Bug: chromedriver:3148\n\u003e Change-Id: I5e8493f4cca48ebaeb211c95cd7fd645891c8659\n\u003e Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1824005\n\u003e Reviewed-by: Andrey Kosyakov \u003ccaseq@chromium.org\u003e\n\u003e Commit-Queue: John Chen \u003cjohnchen@chromium.org\u003e\n\u003e Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#699890}\n\nBug: chromedriver:3148\nChange-Id: I96ce5e6746af65e01407e7c6c92fed7428d686ec\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1829802\nReviewed-by: Eric Seckler \u003ceseckler@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Robert Ma \u003crobertma@chromium.org\u003e\nCommit-Queue: John Chen \u003cjohnchen@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#701614}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: cfa91b8cdf20d0d2ff4531b16d0800cc2ed2a598\nwpt-pr: 19377\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/permissions/set.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7c0ec840ec758328aca379b2f14d43b022109be8", "parents": ["1de6caa2ec6e26a346752578c1ecc2966f195972"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1584612 [wpt PR 19377] - Update wpt metadata, a=testonly\n\nwpt-pr: 19377\nwpt-type: metadata\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/webdriver/tests/permissions/set.py.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "92de08c4fecf6e0f06c1fa5f99a68aa8892b3c95", "parents": ["7c0ec840ec758328aca379b2f14d43b022109be8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587006 [wpt PR 19564] - Test removing a box before a self-collapsing block with clearance., a=testonly\n\nAutomatic update from web-platform-tests\nTest removing a box before a self-collapsing block with clearance.\n\nThis broke for M77 and got fixed again after the branch point. Looks\nlike we had no test coverage for it, but it affected WhatsApp for web.\n\nA phantom line [1] was also required to reproduce the bug.\n\n[1] https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS22/visuren.html#phantom-line-box\n\nBug: 1003810\nChange-Id: I942aea83bbf71a247cf73332dcf62af7c9343106\nReviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1845759\nCommit-Queue: Morten Stenshorne \u003cmstensho@chromium.org\u003e\nReviewed-by: Ian Kilpatrick \u003cikilpatrick@chromium.org\u003e\nCr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/master@{#703899}\n\n--\n\nwpt-commits: 73c311708b30504eb007437234eaa64a9fc6b2bf\nwpt-pr: 19564\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/CSS2/floats-clear/remove-block-before-self-collapsing-sibling-with-clearance.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "daaba9ec234533758002ce72c41de13706842c77", "parents": ["92de08c4fecf6e0f06c1fa5f99a68aa8892b3c95"], "tags": []}, {"author": "moz-wptsync-bot \u003cwptsync@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1588508 - [wpt-sync] Update web-platform-tests to 73c311708b30504eb007437234eaa64a9fc6b2bf, a=testonly\n\nMANUAL PUSH: wpt sync bot\n\nwpt-head: 73c311708b30504eb007437234eaa64a9fc6b2bf\nwpt-type: landing\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/2dcontext/imagebitmap/createImageBitmap-serializable.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/background-fetch/port-blocking.https.window.js.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/compression/decompression-constructor-error.any.js.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/content-security-policy/embedded-enforcement/subsumption_algorithm-hashes.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/CSS2/positioning/relpos-percentage-top-in-scrollable.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-ui/appearance-auto-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-ui/appearance-button-bevel-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-ui/appearance-textfield-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-variables/variable-presentation-attribute.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-writing-modes/writing-mode-vertical-rl-002.xht.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/cssom-view/scrollLeft-of-scroller-with-wider-scrollbar.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/selectors/focus-visible-005.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/text3/segment-break-transformation-removable-3.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/vendor-imports/mozilla/mozilla-central-reftests/text3/segment-break-transformation-removable-4.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/feature-policy/experimental-features/lazyload/lazyload-disabled-tentative.sub.html.ini", "test