32dbfd1a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1589867 - Fix browser_parsable_css.js failure on beta. r=Honza, a=pascalc\n\nThe rotate property is only enabled on Nightly.\nFor beta, we need to use transform: rotate instead.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49847", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/components/App.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f73754c835e0a0a6c0581e28072c098ea0cb3412", "parents": ["461b645866ef930d751777ed7c991f753176d327"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Christoph Kerschbaumer \u003cckerschb@christophkerschbaumer.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1583044: Make nsMozIconURI serializeable. r=valentin, a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49442", "files": ["dom/security/test/crashtests/1583044.html", "dom/security/test/crashtests/crashtests.list", "image/decoders/icon/nsIconURI.cpp", "image/decoders/icon/nsIconURI.h", "netwerk/build/nsNetCID.h", "testing/crashtest/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "17098c3c12fee7b13559acd8976c7fb9f2715187", "parents": ["f73754c835e0a0a6c0581e28072c098ea0cb3412"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1588248 - XHR.send() on workers must throw an InvalidStateError if called during another xhr.send(), r=smaug, a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49968", "files": ["dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestWorker.cpp", "dom/xhr/tests/mochitest.ini", "dom/xhr/tests/test_worker_xhr_doubleSend.html", "dom/xhr/tests/xhr_worker_doubleSend.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6252f0b78cf5c4ab8b52294b2b971746eac4697a", "parents": ["17098c3c12fee7b13559acd8976c7fb9f2715187"], "tags": []}], "date": 1571840328, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "12195": {"changesets": [{"author": "Christian Holler \u003ccholler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504136 - Suppress several leaks in web-platform tests. r=mccr8, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49935", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/pointerevents/__dir__.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "191ba687e88d6583204db3f8426a465b7e2965e1", "parents": ["6252f0b78cf5c4ab8b52294b2b971746eac4697a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1582020 - Minimize time between adb.py's OKAY and exit. r=jdescottes, a=test-only\n\ntest_adb.js is likely failing because the socket is still in use.\nRefactor the code to exit ASAP, by ungracefully exiting adb.py.\nThis logic is also used by the actual adb binary:\nhttps://android.googlesource.com/platform/system/core/+/727b07b2607c712cfa14808de7fcd0d18f5e4923/adb/adb.cpp#1039\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49864", "files": ["devtools/shared/adb/test/adb.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "05079d845b4e98b63b16c063549370ead179011a", "parents": ["191ba687e88d6583204db3f8426a465b7e2965e1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "John Dai \u003cjdai@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1543231 - Fix intermittent dom/html/test/test_bug1472426.html; r=smaug, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49904", "files": ["dom/base/nsMappedAttributes.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ffffab2f48456a25e29dd232f017b19f43abf596", "parents": ["05079d845b4e98b63b16c063549370ead179011a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Naz\u0131m Can Alt\u0131nova \u003ccanaltinova@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1587907 - Move test content inside the BrowserTestUtils.withNewTab function callback. r=gregtatum, a=test-only\n\nIn Bug 1587907 we got some contentPid not found errors. It seemed like we were\nfailing intermittently at getting content pid. After moving test content inside\nthe BrowserTestUtils.withNewTab callback, we won't get the same error anymore.\nAlso from my testing, it looks like it makes the test execution faster. We were\ngetting some intermittents before because of the timeouts, these will be fixed\nif my testing is correct.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49951", "files": ["tools/profiler/tests/browser/browser_test_profile_multi_frame_page_info.js", "tools/profiler/tests/browser/browser_test_profile_single_frame_page_info.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37683e9560d2b6dbe26aba50fecb6439b12a5d57", "parents": ["ffffab2f48456a25e29dd232f017b19f43abf596"], "tags": []}], "date": 1571841932, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "12196": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585931 - don't use subpixel positioning for Fontconfig fonts if full hinting is requested. r=jfkthame a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49901", "files": ["gfx/2d/ScaledFontFontconfig.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFT2FontBase.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c8ab20957ee7e6b535eb8c02f7a0e380f566501b", "parents": ["37683e9560d2b6dbe26aba50fecb6439b12a5d57"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1576568 - Enable editor mode everywhere. r=Honza. a=pascalc\n\nThe focus previous element function needed to be modified\nin order to not find non-visible elements.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D49729", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/components/App.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/components/Input/JSTerm.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/constants.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/reducers/prefs.js", "devtools/clien