umper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\neo -\u003e 908eda66ffda", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "674d9e106294d963caf9366d42138499d0f5b928", "parents": ["49b76d6e3b3af9f73a4594c42a619ed429e16e1c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1574193644, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "12335": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\neo -\u003e bcb32facf9e8\nes-AR -\u003e 8979b3c9d8ab\nes-CL -\u003e ebfe870a3df2\ntrs -\u003e 5c953a6a2b3e\nvi -\u003e 3696042b720a", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fce3628dad6e5e50946ecc46a38739055a6c3e56", "parents": ["674d9e106294d963caf9366d42138499d0f5b928"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\neo -\u003e bcb32facf9e8\nes-AR -\u003e 8979b3c9d8ab\nes-CL -\u003e ebfe870a3df2\ntrs -\u003e 5c953a6a2b3e\nvi -\u003e 3696042b720a", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7b883712ca5d942c19a17da188cae60f65da22b", "parents": ["fce3628dad6e5e50946ecc46a38739055a6c3e56"], "tags": []}], "date": 1574233246, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "12336": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\neu -\u003e 92c4e071bab6\nhu -\u003e 9d5cb2faa4b7\ntr -\u003e 4cea69921c12", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c63095d866d85fc5ee7570ef9d8fb81a1016cc8d", "parents": ["f7b883712ca5d942c19a17da188cae60f65da22b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\neu -\u003e 92c4e071bab6\nhu -\u003e 9d5cb2faa4b7\ntr -\u003e 4cea69921c12", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a9fd74a2e9845a71be5efcaab145ca395a7b02d6", "parents": ["c63095d866d85fc5ee7570ef9d8fb81a1016cc8d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1574258445, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "12337": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1593865 - Simplify code for keeping alive shared memory until all sheets go away. r=jwatt, a=RyanVM\n\nThe existing code wasn't sound, as CSSOM objects also needed to go away before\nthe shared memory goes away (as they keep references to them).\n\nThis is sound assuming no presence of reference cycles introduced by CSSOM.\n\nWe may want to live with this and rely on chrome code not writing cycles like\nthis with UA stylesheet DOM objects.\n\nWe could explicitly drop all potentially-static objects... That seems pretty\nerror prone though.\n\nOr we could also just leak the shared memory buffer, is there any reason why we\nmay not want to do that?\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D51870", "files": ["layout/style/StyleSheet.cpp", "layout/style/StyleSheet.h", "layout/style/StyleSheetInfo.h", "layout/style/nsLayoutStylesheetCache.cpp", "layout/style/nsLayoutStylesheetCache.h", "servo/components/servo_arc/lib.rs", "servo/components/style/stylesheets/stylesheet.rs", "servo/ports/geckolib/glue.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8be50e832d198f1a72c007e4f5075790060d4b48", "parents": ["a9fd74a2e9845a71be5efcaab145ca395a7b02d6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1593865 - Leak shared memory for the lifetime of the process. r=heycam, a=RyanVM\n\nSeems less gnarly than the alternatives, and we'd only free it until shutdown so\nnot much worse, actually.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D51871", "files": ["layout/style/nsLayoutStylesheetCache.cpp", "layout/style/nsLayoutStylesheetCache.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a072e832dee266cccf53d103053a575ac4e48eca", "parents": ["8be50e832d198f1a72c007e4f5075790060d4b48"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1594181 - Reset external variable properly on destruction. r=mccr8, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D52639", "files": ["dom/media/mediacapabilities/BenchmarkStorageChild.cpp", "dom/media/mediacapabilities/BenchmarkStorageChild.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e34e3ab748ad5d7d6cbd6ce9324c12c18305cdc4", "parents": ["a072e832dee266cccf53d103053a575ac4e48eca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1585106 - Use mutex in PACResolver when accessing mRequest from multiple threads. r=michal, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D52488", "files": ["netwerk/base/ProxyAutoConfig.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "25aba0c1d11f32d766304c598e4ec201617f7c44", "parents": ["e34e3ab748ad5d7d6cbd6ce9324c12c18305cdc4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1574283079, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "12338": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597543 - Don't try and associate memory if we failed to create the reflector object r=bzbarsky a=pascalc\n\nThe problem is we're still calling JS::AddAssociatedMemory with a null object pointer. There's an asssertion for this in the JS engine but this doesn't happen in our tests.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53813", "files": ["dom/bindings/BindingUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "040f9f23179e0937043b39699bb11fe1013851a4", "parents": ["25aba0c1d11f32d766304c598e4ec201617f7c44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597265 - Explicitly mark abuse report panel buttons as type button. r=mstriemer a=pascalc\n\nAny button inside a form is by spec considered a submit button\n(as mentioned here https://www.w3.org/TR/html401/interact/forms.html#h-17.5)\nand so, when Enter was pressed while the form was focused, a click event\nwas being triggered on the first button found inside the form\n(and the first button was the hidden close icon button).\n\nExplicitly marking all the report panel buttons as type=\"button\" prevent\nthe report panel from being wrongly cancelled in these scenarios.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53633", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/abuse-report-frame.html", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_abuse_report_dialog.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3ce0374ecdd0ded4ed39401f54ef36a6c99a28ff", "parents": ["040f9f23179e0937043b39699bb11fe1013851a4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrei Oprea \u003candrei.br92@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597706 - Remove the What's new toolbar badge message r=k88hudson a=pascalc\n\nReviewers: k88hudson\n\nReviewed By: k88hudson\n\nBug #: 1597706\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D54008", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/lib/OnboardingMessageProvider.jsm", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/lib/ToolbarBadgeHub.test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "131d053fd24190981cce6dc4736ffc947e2a9be6", "parents": ["3ce0374ecdd0ded4ed39401f54ef36a6c99a28ff"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Scott \u003cscott.downe@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1593290 - Turn on personalization for DS r=gvn a=pascalc\n\nReviewers: gvn\n\nReviewed By: gvn\n\nBug #: 1593290\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53656", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/lib/ActivityStream.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7d09bd1c9a087e3538e5fcc1fa4e466eae67cb61", "parents": ["131d053fd24190981cce6dc4736ffc947e2a9be6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Walsh \u003cdwalsh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1595413 - Revert debugger min-width to fix resizing r=jlast a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D52836", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/src/components/App.css", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/SecondaryPanes/index.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f0fe05870beb9fec9ad28c7d9168bdfa1accba11", "parents": ["7d09bd1c9a087e3538e5fcc1fa4e466eae67cb61"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597043: RootAccessible::ProcessDOMEvent: Return early if AsXULMultiSelectControl() on a XUL tree element fails. r=MarcoZ a=pascalc\n\nThis really shouldn't be possible.\nAll XUL trees should have nsIDOMXULMultiSelectControlElement, and the tree is focused at this point, so it shouldn't be dying.\nNevertheless, this sometimes happens in the wild and was causing crashes.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53373", "files": ["accessible/generic/RootAccessible.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5bc687cb1607f892f5f70842a061b7d3a1efd503", "parents": ["f0fe05870beb9fec9ad28c7d9168bdfa1accba11"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Francesco Lodolo (:flod) \u003cflod@lodolo.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597573 - Add trs to availableLocaleDisplayNames in mozIntl.jsm r=Pike a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53781", "files": ["toolkit/components/mozintl/mozIntl.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "574cae0fc04d927b2286a155d71cf02a7520a33d", "parents": ["5bc687cb1607f892f5f70842a061b7d3a1efd503"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lina Cambridge \u003clina@yakshaving.ninja\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597579 - Back bug 1588005 out of Beta only. r=mythmon a=pascalc\n\nSummary:\nWe have two weeks left until 71 release, and haven't rolled out new\nbookmark sync to everyone yet. Let's disable this in 71 by default\n(but have it ride the train in 72+), and flip it on for everyone in\n70 and 71 using Normandy.\n\nBug #: 1597579\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53872", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "af6a8c0ed2a4424a5bb02a7199dfe021ba810352", "parents": ["574cae0fc04d927b2286a155d71cf02a7520a33d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Scott \u003cscott.downe@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1594173 - Add Ad Privacy Info Modal to Top Sites Tile r=gvn a=pascalc\n\nReviewers: gvn\n\nReviewed By: gvn\n\nBug #: 1594173\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53652", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/TopSites/TopSitesConstants.js", "browser/components/newtab/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f26871df3887f797194f4cc8fa8958801832f9b2", "parents": ["af6a8c0ed2a4424a5bb02a7199dfe021ba810352"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597273 - Handle logical shorthand animations with variable references correctly. r=hiro a=pascalc\n\nWhen we physicalize the declarations for @keyframes, we end up having a physical\ndeclaration with an unparsed value with `from_shorthand` being the logical\nshorthand.\n\nAccount for this case properly when substituting custom properties, to avoid\npanicking.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53663", "files": ["servo/components/style/properties/data.py", "servo/components/style/properties/properties.mako.rs", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-logical/animation-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-logical/animation-002.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f979fad36ca3122de7cd9fd350e88d03188108fc", "parents": ["f26871df3887f797194f4cc8fa8958801832f9b2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1596728 - fix an error when opening a color picker for an element with a pseudo child. r=rcaliman a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53673", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/inspector/utils.js", "devtools/server/tests/browser/browser.ini", "devtools/server/tests/browser/browser_inspector-utils.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4fc0e2524f47fe66062758f9e5ce90737486d56", "parents": ["f979fad36ca3122de7cd9fd350e88d03188108fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1595647 - fix flash permissions so they get set for the toplevel page's principal instead of the subframe, r=mconley a=pascalc\n\nThis is the historical behaviour here (cf. bug 1305232, bug 853855). I accidentally\nbroke it when I refactored this code for fission. This restores the \"old\" behaviour.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53351", "files": ["browser/actors/PluginParent.jsm", "browser/base/content/test/plugins/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/plugins/browser_plugin_framed_domain.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3191228990dac5ecc15b3a4f98cec3fcf50a3f05", "parents": ["f4fc0e2524f47fe66062758f9e5ce90737486d56"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1596065 - Hide database enumeration option in about:support if the pref is off. r=chunmin a=pascalc\n\nWrap around the pref `media.mediacapabilities.from-database` the option to enumerate MediaCapabilities database in `about:support` page. When the pref is off the button disappears and the enumeration method returns early.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53008", "files": ["toolkit/content/aboutSupport.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "75ad02f5fe90f091353dd4b1fd15308857411b2e", "parents": ["3191228990dac5ecc15b3a4f98cec3fcf50a3f05"], "tags": []}, {"author": "harry \u003chtwyford@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1595082 - Ensure every Touch Bar input is updated at least once. r=mikedeboer,spohl a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53176", "files": ["browser/components/touchbar/MacTouchBar.js", "widget/cocoa/nsTouchBarUpdater.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1568ccf6781254d6cc0aa6ed43e247e1ac56687c", "parents": ["75ad02f5fe90f091353dd4b1fd15308857411b2e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Doug Thayer \u003cdothayer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1594051 - Perform fallible alloc when copying buffer from StartupCache r=froydnj a=pascalc\n\nThis effectively used to be a fallible alloc inside nsZipArchive.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D52199", "files": ["js/xpconnect/loader/mozJSLoaderUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c98db28b8d9e2b9b4ba07a203d8e81e74b9cfa6d", "parents": ["1568ccf6781254d6cc0aa6ed43e247e1ac56687c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1592600 - fix prefs link in about:addons to ignore hashes/fragments as well as right clicks, r=mstriemer a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D51286", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/preferences.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "689b44219fabbb127cb24a5c7f3d8595f64bcf24", "parents": ["c98db28b8d9e2b9b4ba07a203d8e81e74b9cfa6d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1574341288, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rgurzau@mozilla.com"}, "12339": {"changesets": [{"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1597928 - Snap repackage: Stop fetching scripts from the hg.mozilla.org archive endpoint. r=jlund, a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D53933", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-snap-repackage/kind.yml", "taskcluster/docker/firefox-snap/Dockerfile"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e68959e896eabf7ccddd81a86655139b91fd82e2", "parents": ["689b44219fabbb127cb24a5c7f3d8595f64bcf24"], "tags": []}], "date": 1574342559, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jcristau@mozilla.com"}, "12340": {"changesets": [{"author": "J.C. Jones \u003cjc@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1588559 - land NSS NSS_3_47_1_RTM UPGRADE_NSS_RELEASE, r=kjacobs a=pascalc\n\n2019-11-19  J.C. Jones  \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e\n\n\t* lib/nss/nss.h, lib/softoken/softkver.h, lib/util/nssutil.h:\n\tSet version numbers to 3.47.1 final\n\t[6339a6f350c9] [NSS_3_47_1_RTM] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\n2019-11-19  Craig Disselkoen  \u003ccdisselk@cs.ucsd.edu\u003e\n\n\t* lib/softoken/pkcs11c.c:\n\tBug 1586176 - EncryptUpdate should use maxout not block size.\n\tr=franziskus\n\t[4c20de402b39] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\n2019-10-21  Marcus Burghardt  \u003cmburghardt@mozilla.com\u003e\n\n\t* lib/ckfw/builtins/testlib/certdata-testlib.txt:\n\tBug 1589810 - Uninitialized variable warnings from certdata.perl.\n\tr=mt\n\n\t[86f505b65576] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\n2019-11-04  Marcus Burghardt  \u003cmburghardt@mozilla.com\u003e\n\n\t* lib/pk11wrap/pk11cert.c:\n\tBug 1590495 - Crash in PK11_MakeCertFromHandle-\u003epk11_fastCert. r=jcj\n\n\tFixed controls to avoid crashes caused by slots possibly without a\n\ttoken in pk11_fastCert. Also, improved arguments controls in\n\tPK11_MakeCertFromHandle.\n\n\t[54ce0e2caeb8] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\n2019-11-11  Tom Prince  \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e\n\n\t* automation/taskcluster/graph/src/extend.js,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/windows/setup.sh:\n\tBug 1594891 - Use tc-proxy for nss tooltool; r=dustin,jcj\n\n\t[15b525236995] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\n2019-11-08  Dustin J. Mitchell  \u003cdustin@mozilla.com\u003e\n\n\t* automation/taskcluster/graph/npm-shrinkwrap.json,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/graph/package.json,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/graph/src/image_builder.js,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/graph/src/queue.js,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/scripts/tools.sh,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/windows/gen_certs.sh,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/windows/run_tests.sh:\n\tBug 1594891 - Updates to run correctly on the new TC deployment\n\tr=jcj\n\n\t* Update the Taskcluster client used in the decision task to one\n\tthat understands Taskcluster rootUrls.\n\t* Update scripts that fetch content to use the TASKCLUSTER_ROOT_URL\n\t  * the absence of this variale signals an \"old\" worker so we use an\n\t\"old\" URL\n\n\t[054c57351ca0] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\n2019-11-07  Tom Prince  \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e\n\n\t* .taskcluster.yml, automation/taskcluster/graph/src/extend.js,\n\tautomation/taskcluster/graph/src/queue.js:\n\tBug 1591275: Switch workers to use AWS Provder; r=kjacobs\n\n\t[af55d9185ec5] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\n2019-10-18  J.C. Jones  \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e\n\n\t* .hgtags:\n\tAdded tag NSS_3_47_RTM for changeset 7ccb4ade5577\n\t[dcadb95b9d77] \u003cNSS_3_47_BRANCH\u003e\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabrica